{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778672628500,"sessionID":"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_FjpRmkLTBOs1rerCH1aKmqje","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\n+title: \"Drop stale load-select control\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already registers the final MEM/WB wb_data, so the old\n+  load writeback select no longer fans into the writeback, forwarding, or RVFI\n+  rd_wdata paths. However ctrl_t.mem_to_reg is still decoded, latched through\n+  ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB, and routed alongside hotter control fields. Prior\n+  metadata-pruning wins show this FPGA build benefits when unnecessary control\n+  routing is removed, while broad structural changes have recently hurt Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg and use the existing local load control in mem_stage\n+  to select between sign/zero-extended load_data and the EX/MEM alu_result when\n+  forming the registered wb_data. This revisits the earlier load-select pruning\n+  only after the successful final-wb-data retiming, so the selector no longer\n+  affects the regfile, MEM/WB forwarding, or RVFI writeback fanout. CPI should\n+  stay unchanged, and the narrower control bundle may improve Tang Nano 20K\n+  placement/routing enough to lift median Fmax.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the now-redundant ctrl_t.mem_to_reg field from the shared pipeline control bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the mem_to_reg output and assignments while preserving load legality, mem_read, reg_write, width, and sign controls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove decoder mem_to_reg wiring and stop populating the eliminated control bit in ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Select registered wb_data with the local load indication instead of ctrl.mem_to_reg, keeping RVFI memory fields and store buffering unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\n+title: \"Drop stale load-select control\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already registers the final MEM/WB wb_data, so the old\n+  load writeback select no longer fans into the writeback, forwarding, or RVFI\n+  rd_wdata paths. However ctrl_t.mem_to_reg is still decoded, latched through\n+  ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB, and routed alongside hotter control fields. Prior\n+  metadata-pruning wins show this FPGA build benefits when unnecessary control\n+  routing is removed, while broad structural changes have recently hurt Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg and use the existing local load control in mem_stage\n+  to select between sign/zero-extended load_data and the EX/MEM alu_result when\n+  forming the registered wb_data. This revisits the earlier load-select pruning\n+  only after the successful final-wb-data retiming, so the selector no longer\n+  affects the regfile, MEM/WB forwarding, or RVFI writeback fanout. CPI should\n+  stay unchanged, and the narrower control bundle may improve Tang Nano 20K\n+  placement/routing enough to lift median Fmax.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the now-redundant ctrl_t.mem_to_reg field from the shared pipeline control bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the mem_to_reg output and assignments while preserving load legality, mem_read, reg_write, width, and sign controls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove decoder mem_to_reg wiring and stop populating the eliminated control bit in ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Select registered wb_data with the local load indication instead of ctrl.mem_to_reg, keeping RVFI memory fields and store buffering unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r11s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r11s0\n+title: \"Drop stale load-select control\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already registers the final MEM/WB wb_data, so the old\n+  load writeback select no longer fans into the writeback, forwarding, or RVFI\n+  rd_wdata paths. However ctrl_t.mem_to_reg is still decoded, la