_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":57294,\"input\":920,\"output\":54,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":56320}},\"cost\":0}}\n\n(End of file - total 21 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778672566669,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2125818c001Rq4vZ3O3Y8CWxq\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e21257db3001Xb1FsbbMCQZtl1\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"snapshot\":\"6474674c31e5df5d27c6accb9f31f32faeeeb155\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1778672576586,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e21258f5f0010SKbZhusd56nAH\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e21257db3001Xb1FsbbMCQZtl1\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I’ll check the existing lessons/log for prior `micro_opt` attempts, then write the hypothesis YAML under `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/` with the required short file paths.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1778672570207,\"end\":1778672576585},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_003180534bf446ef016a0463ba1974819b9498458b37185790\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778672576600,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_OSOvkYbfqjqcdIpaPuHNxJtZ\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/LESSONS.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":200},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/LESSONS.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r1s0 (improvement, +11.81%): Avoid resetting RV32I regfile backing arrays when x0 is enforced by read/write gating, because reset fanout can block LUTRAM-friendly inference and hurt FPGA Fmax without improving initialized CoreMark code.\\n2: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-002-r1s1 (regression, -30.56%): ID-stage branch resolution needs real EX/MEM operand bypasses to help CoreMark counted loops; conservatively disabling early redirects on any in-flight producer mostly preserves the EX penalty while adding front-end control/comparison cost.\\n3: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r1s2 (broken, n/a): Fetch prediction cannot simply suppress the existing EX redirect on correctly predicted branches; the speculative IF/ID path must still preserve RVFI branch pc_wdata/pc_fwd semantics and flush only proven wrong-path instructions.\\n4: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r2s0 (broken, n/a): Load-use source qualification should stay in the stall path unless RVFI source reporting is updated coherently; zeroing ID-stage rs*_addr/rs*_rdata for “unused” operands can break riscv-formal's reg check even when the datapath dependency is false.\\n5: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-002-r2s1 (improvement, +12.85%): Moving rare RV32M multiply/divide operations into a stalling multicycle MDU can improve Tang Nano 20K fitness because CoreMark's hot RV32I-heavy EX path benefits more from removing multiplier/divider cones than it loses to occasional M-op latency.\\n6: - 2026-05-13 hyp... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778672576605,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_cHvH3vURRusdmpgiRSjjFfYT\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"\\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\"|category: micro_opt|micro_opt|Register final writeback|forward|wb_data|regfile|critical|Fmax\",\"path\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments\",\"include\":\"log.jsonl\"},\"output\":\"Found 28 matches\\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl:\\n  Line 1: {\\\"id\\\": \\\"baseline-bench-2bcada9\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Baseline retest for cores/bench\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\", \\\"outcome\\\": \\\"improvement\\\", \\\"fitness\\\": 282.82, \\\"delta_pct\\\": 0.0, \\\"vs_baseline\\\": 0.0, \\\"fmax_mhz\\\": 127.03, \\\"ipc_coremark\\\": 2e-06, \\\"cycles\\\": 4491485, \\\"iterations\\\": 10, \\\"lut4\\\": 9563, \\\"ff\\\": 1866, \\\"seeds\\\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \\\"formal_passed\\\": true, \\\"cosim_passed\\\": true, \\\"error\\\": null, \\\"implementation_notes\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-05-13T07:26:50.420685Z\\\", \\\"round_id\\\": 0, \\\"slot\\\": 0}\\n\\n  Line 2: {\\\"id\\\": \\\"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Remove regfile reset fanout\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\", \\\"motivation\\\": \\\"The current register file resets all 32 architectural registers with a\\\\nsynchronous for-loop. On FPGA this discourages LUTRAM-style inference for the\\\\n32x32 storage and adds reset muxing/fanout across a hot, frequently accessed\\\\nstructure. RV32I does not require integer registers other than x0 to have a\\\\ndefined reset value, and x0 is already hardwired through read/write gating.\\\\n\\\", \\\"hypothesis\\\": {\\\"motivation\\\": \\\"The current register file resets all 32 architectural registers with a\\\\nsynchronous for-loop. On FPGA this discourages LUTRAM-style inference for the\\\\n32x32 storage and adds reset muxing/fanout across a hot, frequently accessed\\\\nstructure. RV32I does not re... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778672576658,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2125a891001a1wGGfSNHD4Q62\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"6474674c31e5df5d27c6accb9f31f32faeeeb155\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e21257db3001Xb1FsbbMCQZtl1\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":40002,\"input\":30017,\"output\":223,\"reasoning\":34,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":9728}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778672577736,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2125acc7001gnyoVLtvFAqGq6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2125a8b60014W4bLvESvelhdz\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"snapshot\":\"6474674c31e5df5d27c6accb9f31f32faeeeb155\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1778672599727,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2125fda90013jzsMnIYOQMnfx\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2125a8b60014W4bLvESvelhdz\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The log confirms the productive `micro_opt` pattern is removing hot-path/reset/metadata pressure, while front-end predictors and wider control changes consistently regressed. I’m going to target the now-redundant `mem_to_reg` control bit in the post-`wb_data` design, where the prior fanout risk is narrower than before.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1778672598441,\"end\":1778672599726},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_0214485d86f02537016a0463d654288199b8d59edb802b1714\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778672601810,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_dqJ4VfDxKulEASNVSQ4ucQAE\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/*.yaml\",\"path\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1\"},\"output\":\"No files found\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":0,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"\",\"time\":{\"start\":1778672601797,\"end\":1778672601810}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_0214485d86f02537016a0463d79d588199a777d93ea07a3f61\"}},\"id\":\"prt_e212602af0029XJXxtfcXtYoGM\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1deda82a2ffez38tvd0BEbpVJ2\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2125a8b60014W4bLvESvelhdz\"}}\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timest