{"type":"text","timestamp":1778674579010,"sessionID":"ses_1debd2610ffeK92VxWxUy2pGK7","part":{"id":"prt_e21443251001yqdUogjopyppFc","messageID":"msg_e21440f75001wDk2y58upTlTzz","sessionID":"ses_1debd2610ffeK92VxWxUy2pGK7","type":"text","text":"I found the `mem_to_reg` idea already exists in the historical log, so I’m switching to a distinct micro-opt: pre-gating x0-producing writes/forwards once at the producer sideband, then removing repeated zero-destination checks from the forwarding and regfile write paths.","time":{"start":1778674578001,"end":1778674579009},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02c720d87f6ecb7e016a046b91d0f8819ba9ee618d32b4895c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778674600645,"sessionID":"ses_1debd2610ffeK92VxWxUy2pGK7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_mWhhtqDZbWKSRZQOiXXpPa2W","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Pre-gate x0 producer enables\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent successful changes reduced routing pressure on hot back-end paths\n+  without changing CPI, while predictor and broader control rewrites usually\n+  lost Fmax. The current core still repeats zero-register destination checks in\n+  several producer-consumer cones: writeback asserts w_en for rd=x0 and relies\n+  on reg_file to suppress it, forwarding sideband enables are true for rd=x0\n+  and forward_unit rechecks rd!=0 for both operands, and RVFI computes its own\n+  rd write-enable predicate.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Gate x0-producing instructions once when creating producer enables: make the\n+  WB-stage write enable include rd!=0, make EX/MEM and MEM/WB forwarding\n+  sideband enables include rd!=0, and then remove the duplicate rd!=0 checks\n+  from forward_unit and the reg_file write port. Keep x0 read-as-zero behavior\n+  and RVFI rd_addr/rd_wdata suppression unchanged. This should slightly shorten\n+  the forwarding compare/control cone and reduce small repeated comparators on\n+  a timing-sensitive design, with no change to pipeline timing, memory ordering,\n+  trap behavior, or the nret=1 top-level interface.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pre-gate exmem_fwd_en and memwb_fwd_en with rd!=0, and reuse the already gated writeback predicate where safe for RVFI writeback reporting.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove duplicate destination-nonzero checks because producer forwarding enables are already x0-suppressed.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Make w_en assert only for valid register writes with rd!=0 so downstream regfile logic no longer needs to suppress x0 writes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the redundant w_addr!=0 write guard while preserving x0 read-as-zero priority and same-cycle write-first bypass for nonzero registers.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Pre-gate x0 producer enables\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent successful changes reduced routing pressure on hot back-end paths\n+  without changing CPI, while predictor and broader control rewrites usually\n+  lost Fmax. The current core still repeats zero-register destination checks in\n+  several producer-consumer cones: writeback asserts w_en for rd=x0 and relies\n+  on reg_file to suppress it, forwarding sideband enables are true for rd=x0\n+  and forward_unit rechecks rd!=0 for both operands, and RVFI computes its own\n+  rd write-enable predicate.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Gate x0-producing instructions once when creating producer enables: make the\n+  WB-stage write enable include rd!=0, make EX/MEM and MEM/WB forwarding\n+  sideband enables include rd!=0, and then remove the duplicate rd!=0 checks\n+  from forward_unit and the reg_file write port. Keep x0 read-as-zero behavior\n+  and RVFI rd_addr/rd_wdata suppression unchanged. This should slightly shorten\n+  the forwarding compare/control cone and reduce small repeated comparators on\n+  a timing-sensitive design, with no change to pipeline timing, memory ordering,\n+  trap behavior, or the nret=1 top-level interface.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pre-gate exmem_fwd_en and memwb_fwd_en with rd!=0, and reuse the already gated writeback predicate where safe for RVFI writeback reporting.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Remove duplicate destination-nonzero checks because producer forwarding enables are already x0-suppressed.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Make w_en assert only for valid register writes with rd!=0 so downstream regfile logic no longer needs to suppress x0 writes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the redundant w_addr!=0 write guard while preserving x0 read-as-zero priority and same-cycle write-first bypass for nonzero registers.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1