{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778674606649,"sessionID":"ses_1debd2610ffeK92VxWxUy2pGK7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2fj926yUMgwTgDJUmL8zJ6iG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\n2: title: \"Pre-gate x0 producer enables\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Recent successful changes reduced routing pressure on hot back-end paths\n6:   without changing CPI, while predictor and broader control rewrites usually\n7:   lost Fmax. The current core still repeats zero-register destination checks in\n8:   several producer-consumer cones: writeback asserts w_en for rd=x0 and relies\n9:   on reg_file to suppress it, forwarding sideband enables are true for rd=x0\n10:   and forward_unit rechecks rd!=0 for both operands, and RVFI computes its own\n11:   rd write-enable predicate.\n12: hypothesis: |\n13:   Gate x0-producing instructions once when creating producer enables: make the\n14:   WB-stage write enable include rd!=0, make EX/MEM and MEM/WB forwarding\n15:   sideband enables include rd!=0, and then remove the duplicate rd!=0 checks\n16:   from forward_unit and the reg_file write port. Keep x0 read-as-zero behavior\n17:   and RVFI rd_addr/rd_wdata suppression unchanged. This should slightly shorten\n18:   the forwarding compare/control cone and reduce small repeated comparators on\n19:   a timing-sensitive design, with no change to pipeline timing, memory ordering,\n20:   trap behavior, or the nret=1 top-level interface.\n21: expected_impact:\n22:   fitness_delta_pct: 1\n23:   confidence: medium\n24: changes:\n25:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n26:     description: \"Pre-gate exmem_fwd_en and memwb_fwd_en with rd!=0, and reuse the already gated writeback predicate where safe for RVFI writeback reporting.\"\n27:   - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n28:     description: \"Remove duplicate destination-nonzero checks because producer forwarding enables are already x0-suppressed.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Make w_en assert only for valid register writes with rd!=0 so downstream regfile logic no longer needs to suppress x0 writes.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n32:     description: \"Drop the redundant w_addr!=0 write guard while preserving x0 read-as-zero priority and same-cycle write-first bypass for nonzero registers.\"\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\ntitle: \"Pre-gate x0 producer enables\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  Recent successful changes reduced routing pressure on hot back-end paths\n  without changing CPI, while predictor and broader control rewrites usually\n  lost Fmax. The current core still repeats zero-register destination checks in\n  several producer-consumer cones: writeback asserts w_en for rd=x0 and relies\n  on reg_file to suppress it, forwarding sideband enables are true for rd=x0\n  and forward_unit rechecks rd!=0 for both operands, and RVFI computes its own\n  rd write-enable predicate.\nhypothesis: |\n  Gate x0-producing instructions once when creating producer enables: make the\n  WB-stage write enable include rd!=0, make EX/MEM and MEM/WB forwarding\n  sideband enables include rd!=0, and then remove the duplicate rd!=0 checks\n  from forward_unit and the reg_file write port. Keep x0 read-as-zero behavior\n  and RVFI rd_addr/rd_wdata suppression unchanged. This should slightly shorten\n  the forwarding compare/control cone and reduce small repeated comparators on\n  a timing-sensitive design, with no change to pipeline timing, memory ordering,\n  trap behavior, or the nret=1 top-level interface.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778674606646,"end":1778674606649}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cc704cbe5aa4d17016a046babc79c819aac6fa78152cd9b19"}},"id":"prt_e21449766001aVaMGhvxHJi5ou","sessionID":"ses_1debd2610ffeK92VxWxUy2pGK7","messageID":"msg_e21448b5a001jC3ICr4wAz0U1m"}}
