{"type":"text","timestamp":1778675444305,"sessionID":"ses_1deafe322ffefGCJDO9sX04l00","part":{"id":"prt_e21515fa1001Lsv3jGICzzKQUW","messageID":"msg_e215153f8001Dd8icvmKev79LV","sessionID":"ses_1deafe322ffefGCJDO9sX04l00","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a focused micro-opt: remove the now-redundant `mem_to_reg` control bit and select registered `wb_data` from local MEM-stage load control only. This keeps behavior unchanged and targets narrower control routing, matching the successful metadata-pruning pattern without touching prediction or memory protocol.","time":{"start":1778675441569,"end":1778675444304},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03f1f78b4e892a46016a046ef177248199a8e9b5243cb2f6fd","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778675466044,"sessionID":"ses_1deafe322ffefGCJDO9sX04l00","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_OV2sIGHMOed8vpCEpcCUo4jF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\n+title: \"Drop stale load-select control\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core already registers the final MEM/WB wb_data value, so the old\n+  mem_to_reg control bit no longer sits on the regfile write, forwarding, or\n+  RVFI rd_wdata fanout. It is still decoded, carried through every pipeline\n+  control bundle, and used only inside mem_stage to choose the value that is\n+  registered into wb_data. Prior successful bench changes came from pruning\n+  cold metadata and isolating hot sidebands, while broader control repacking and\n+  front-end speculation repeatedly lost Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg entirely and form MEM/WB wb_data from local MEM-stage\n+  load knowledge: loads select the sign/zero-extended load_data, and all other\n+  instructions select the EX/MEM alu_result. This keeps the registered wb_data\n+  retiming intact, avoids increasing mem_read fanout beyond the MEM-stage local\n+  mux, and narrows ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB control routing by one bit.\n+\n+  CPI, memory ordering, trap behavior, RVFI order/reporting, MDU behavior, and\n+  the nret=1 top-level IO should remain unchanged. The expected gain is a small\n+  Tang Nano 20K Fmax lift from deleting stale decode/control plumbing without\n+  adding any new datapath or prediction logic.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the redundant ctrl_t.mem_to_reg field from the shared control bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the mem_to_reg output and assignments while preserving load legality, mem_read, reg_write, width, and sign controls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove decoder mem_to_reg wiring and stop populating the eliminated control bit in ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use local mem_read/load_data selection when registering wb_data, preserving existing RVFI and store-buffer behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\n+title: \"Drop stale load-select control\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core already registers the final MEM/WB wb_data value, so the old\n+  mem_to_reg control bit no longer sits on the regfile write, forwarding, or\n+  RVFI rd_wdata fanout. It is still decoded, carried through every pipeline\n+  control bundle, and used only inside mem_stage to choose the value that is\n+  registered into wb_data. Prior successful bench changes came from pruning\n+  cold metadata and isolating hot sidebands, while broader control repacking and\n+  front-end speculation repeatedly lost Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg entirely and form MEM/WB wb_data from local MEM-stage\n+  load knowledge: loads select the sign/zero-extended load_data, and all other\n+  instructions select the EX/MEM alu_result.