{"type":"text","timestamp":1778676403846,"sessionID":"ses_1dea052f7ffeSpc7FD0NlU0Po7","part":{"id":"prt_e216003f9001X7ZqROHG81RUjn","messageID":"msg_e215fe2b1001gdZ7YAKRp0IeKa","sessionID":"ses_1dea052f7ffeSpc7FD0NlU0Po7","type":"text","text":"The history shows the successful micro-opts were small Fmax/routing reductions, while repeated predictor, control-repacking, load-bypass, and stale `mem_to_reg` pruning attempts regressed. I’m selecting a narrow hot-path cleanup that keeps CPI and metadata unchanged: simplify the EX operand-forward mux encoding from 2-bit selects to direct producer-hit controls, avoiding a standalone select encoder plus downstream decode.","time":{"start":1778676401146,"end":1778676403844},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0123f611f8467dda016a0472b10c988198ba46aa6c0377ab2c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
