{"type":"text","timestamp":1778657271704,"sessionID":"ses_1dfc49f0fffecJpc9qvxOyv2Yx","part":{"id":"prt_e203c1e94001RApeoqMtZ2d8rz","messageID":"msg_e203bb913001cttHEuvyW4rOW7","sessionID":"ses_1dfc49f0fffecJpc9qvxOyv2Yx","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a single-file `micro_opt` hypothesis: remove the integer register file reset so the 32x32 regfile can infer cheaper FPGA storage and avoid reset fanout/muxing, while keeping x0 and write-first behavior intact.","time":{"start":1778657271444,"end":1778657271703},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_096149233e8aec88016a0427f75150819bba71deff11c67fe2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778657275291,"sessionID":"ses_1dfc49f0fffecJpc9qvxOyv2Yx","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_nvQ6cpq38lR2RJCsbCWXgaX9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Remove regfile reset fanout\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current register file resets all 32 architectural registers with a\n+  synchronous for-loop. On FPGA this discourages LUTRAM-style inference for the\n+  32x32 storage and adds reset muxing/fanout across a hot, frequently accessed\n+  structure. RV32I does not require integer registers other than x0 to have a\n+  defined reset value, and x0 is already hardwired through read/write gating.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Change rtl/reg_file.sv so reset no longer clears the backing register array.\n+  Preserve the existing write-first bypass, x0 read-as-zero behavior, and write\n+  suppression to x0. This should reduce flip-flop/reset routing pressure and may\n+  let synthesis map the register file to distributed RAM or a smaller muxed\n+  structure, improving Fmax with negligible CoreMark CPI risk because compiled C\n+  code initializes live registers before use.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the synchronous reset loop over regs[0:31] while preserving x0 hardwiring and write-first read bypass semantics.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n