{"type":"text","timestamp":1778659576986,"sessionID":"ses_1dfa174fdffe4dNMoxP5vUUfWw","part":{"id":"prt_e205f4940001JlMzEIX9w4ZNWX","messageID":"msg_e205ef002001SDStrlcAypifAH","sessionID":"ses_1dfa174fdffe4dNMoxP5vUUfWw","type":"text","text":"A promising `micro_opt` is to remove false load-use stalls: the current hazard unit compares the prior load’s `rd` against both raw `rs1` and `rs2` bitfields for every following instruction, even when those fields are immediates or unused. That can inject unnecessary bubbles after loads without changing correctness.","time":{"start":1778659576128,"end":1778659576985},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_04f869e9c978f241016a0430f805fc81989102909d1ee709b3","phase":"commentary"}}}}
