{"type":"text","timestamp":1778659599643,"sessionID":"ses_1dfa174fdffe4dNMoxP5vUUfWw","part":{"id":"prt_e205f9f3f001Ivf7vBuNNahg1J","messageID":"msg_e205f7cf10012CyGrr3YnDNVFa","sessionID":"ses_1dfa174fdffe4dNMoxP5vUUfWw","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis YAML with short `rtl/...` paths and the required `micro_opt` schema fields.","time":{"start":1778659598143,"end":1778659599642},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_013164423d12a3cc016a04310e0970819ab41de15f8cd1332d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778659622536,"sessionID":"ses_1dfa174fdffe4dNMoxP5vUUfWw","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_HqSoKpRvhfyoKLXdVKY23VIS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Qualify load-use source checks\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use hazard detector compares a load destination against both\n+  raw source bitfields of the following instruction for every opcode. For many\n+  RV32I instructions, one or both of those bitfields are immediate bits or are\n+  otherwise unused, so a coincidental match with the prior load's rd injects a\n+  needless one-cycle bubble. CoreMark has frequent loads followed by immediate\n+  arithmetic, address updates, jumps, and upper-immediate instructions where\n+  avoiding false dependencies should improve iterations per cycle without\n+  touching the proven datapath or memory protocol.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Teach the hazard unit which IF/ID operands are actually consumed before\n+  applying the load-use comparison. Keep the true load-use stall for branches,\n+  stores, R-type operations, JALR, OP-IMM rs1 uses, and real load base-register\n+  dependencies, but ignore rs2 for I-type/load/JALR immediates and ignore both\n+  operands for LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, and EBREAK. This is a small combinational\n+  decode in the existing hazard path that should remove spurious bubbles while\n+  preserving all forwarding, RVFI order, trap, and bus-stall behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Derive IF/ID rs1_used and rs2_used from opcode/funct fields and gate load-use comparisons with those source-use bits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction or equivalent source-use metadata into the hazard unit while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Qualify load-use source checks\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use hazard detector compares a load destination against both\n+  raw source bitfields of the following instruction for every opcode. For many\n+  RV32I instructions, one or both of those bitfields are immediate bits or are\n+  otherwise unused, so a coincidental match with the prior load's rd injects a\n+  needless one-cycle bubble. CoreMark has frequent loads followed by immediate\n+  arithmetic, address updates, jumps, and upper-immediate instructions where\n+  avoiding false dependencies should improve iterations per cycle without\n+  touching the proven datapath or memory protocol.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Teach the hazard unit which IF/ID operands are actually consumed before\n+  applying the load-use comparison. Keep the true load-use stall for branches,\n+  stores, R-type operations, JALR, OP-IMM rs1 uses, and real load base-register\n+  dependencies, but ignore rs2 for I-type/load/JALR immediates and ignore both\n+  operands for LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, and EBREAK. This is a small combinational\n+  decode in the existing hazard path that should remove spurious bubbles while\n+  preserving all forwarding, RVFI order, trap, and bus-stall behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Derive IF/ID rs1_used and rs2_used from opcode/funct fields and gate load-use comparisons with those source-use bits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction or equivalent source-use metadata into the hazard unit while preserving the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Qualify load-use source checks\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use hazard detector compares a load destination against both\n+  raw source bitfields of the following instruction for every opcode. For many\n+  RV32I instructions, one or both of those bitfields are immediate bits or are\n+  otherwise unused, so a coincidental match with the prior load's rd injects a\n+  needless one-cycle bubble. CoreMark has frequent loads followed by immediate\n+  arithmetic, address updates, jumps, and upper-immediate instructions where\n+  avoiding false dependencies should improve iterations per cycle without\n+  touching the proven datapath or memory protocol.\