{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778661532422,"sessionID":"ses_1df852f05ffevO4NRZCxi8ftFH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_mkTYAj7HAWkVfG0cRC7pbOQX","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Prune dead pipeline metadata\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current post-MDU core is Fmax-sensitive enough that small reductions in\n+  pipeline register width and hot-stage routing can still move Tang Nano 20K\n+  fitness. Several metadata fields are carried after decode/execute but are not\n+  consumed by any later stage or by RVFI: LUI is already represented by\n+  alu_op=ALU_LUI plus alu_src, and EX-stage branch_taken/branch_target are only\n+  used locally before being redundantly flopped into EX/MEM.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove dead metadata from the pipeline bundles and the wiring that feeds it:\n+  drop ctrl_t.is_lui and the decoder/id-stage plumbing for it, and drop\n+  ex_mem_t.branch_taken plus ex_mem_t.branch_target and their EX-stage register\n+  assignments. This should reduce flip-flops, mux inputs, and routing pressure\n+  across ID/EX and EX/MEM without changing instruction semantics, branch\n+  redirect timing, memory behavior, or the nret=1 RVFI retirement interface.\n+  Because the change is pure metadata pruning, CPI should be unchanged while\n+  median Fmax may improve modestly.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove unused ctrl_t.is_lui and dead ex_mem_t branch_taken/branch_target fields from the pipeline bundle definitions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the unused is_lui output and its assignments while preserving LUI legality, ALU_LUI selection, alu_src, and reg_write behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove decoder is_lui plumbing and stop assigning the deleted ctrl_t field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep branch_taken and branch_target as local EX combinational signals only; remove dead EX/MEM register assignments.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Clean up stale comments that mention removed EX/MEM branch metadata; no behavioral memory changes.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Prune dead pipeline metadata\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current post-MDU core is Fmax-sensitive enough that small reductions in\n+  pipeline register width and hot-stage routing can still move Tang Nano 20K\n+  fitness. Several metadata fields are carried after decode/execute but are not\n+  consumed by any later stage or by RVFI: LUI is already represented by\n+  alu_op=ALU_LUI plus alu_src, and EX-stage branch_taken/branch_target are only\n+  used locally before being redundantly flopped into EX/MEM.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove dead metadata from the pipeline bundles and the wiring that feeds it:\n+  drop ctrl_t.is_lui and the decoder/id-stage plumbing for it, and drop\n+  ex_mem_t.branch_taken plus ex_mem_t.branch_target and their EX-stage register\n+  assignments. This should reduce flip-flops, mux inputs, and routing pressure\n+  across ID/EX and EX/MEM without chan