{"type":"text","timestamp":1778663218962,"sessionID":"ses_1df6a00f7ffegIolN9Kerr5CUi","part":{"id":"prt_e2096d7460014V04jtGtHp6gKm","messageID":"msg_e209652bf0010NKwMUGzpBs0Zi","sessionID":"ses_1df6a00f7ffegIolN9Kerr5CUi","type":"text","text":"The log confirms the successful micro-opts were low-risk Fmax reductions: regfile reset removal and dead metadata pruning. I’m going to propose a similarly narrow control-bit pruning: remove `ctrl_t.mem_to_reg` and use `mem_read` as the WB load-result selector, since every legal load already asserts both and no non-load uses `mem_to_reg`.","time":{"start":1778663216966,"end":1778663218961},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b444d5462cd769a016a043f30dd788199be44a8f0e422af01","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778663224505,"sessionID":"ses_1df6a00f7ffegIolN9Kerr5CUi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MkGpNvLJ43pgM9HthDr9OMr2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","offset":8,"limit":1},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n8: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\", \"title\": \"Prune dead pipeline metadata\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The current post-MDU core is Fmax-sensitive enough that small reductions in\\npipeline register width and hot-stage routing can still move Tang Nano 20K\\nfitness. Several metadata fields are carried after decode/execute but are not\\nconsumed by any later stage or by RVFI: LUI is already represented by\\nalu_op=ALU_LUI plus alu_src, and EX-stage branch_taken/branch_target are only\\nused locally before being redundantly flopped into EX/MEM.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current post-MDU core is Fmax-sensitive enough that small reductions in\\npipeline register width and hot-stage routing can still move Tang Nano 20K\\nfitness. Several metadata fields are carried after decode/execute but are not\\nconsumed by any later stage or by RVFI: LUI is already represented by\\nalu_op=ALU_LUI plus alu_src, and EX-stage branch_taken/branch_target are only\\nused locally before being redundantly flopped into EX/MEM.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Remove dead metadata from the pipeline bundles and the wiring that feeds it:\\ndrop ctrl_t.is_lui and the decoder/id-stage plumbing for it, and drop\\nex_mem_t.branch_taken plus ex_mem_t.branch_target and their EX-stage register\\nassignments. This should reduce flip-flops, mux inputs, and routing pressure\\nacross ID/EX and EX/MEM without changing instruction semantics, branch\\nredirect timing, memory behavior, or the nret=1 RVFI retirement interface.\\nBecause the change is pure metadata pruning, CPI should be unchanged while\\nmedian Fmax may improve modestly.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove unused ctrl_t.is_lui and dead ex_mem_t branch_taken/branch_target fields from the pipeline bundle definitions.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/decoder.sv\", \"description\": \"Drop the unused is_lui output and its assignments while preserving LUI legality, ALU_LUI select... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(Showing lines 8-8 of 10. Use offset=9 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\", \"title\": \"Prune dead pipeline metadata\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The current post-MDU core is Fmax-sensitive enough that small reductions in\\npipeline register width and hot-stage routing can still move Tang Nano 20K\\nfitness. Several metadata fields are carried after decode/execute but are not\\nconsumed by any later stage or by RVFI: LUI is already represented by\\nalu_op=ALU_LUI plus alu_src, and EX-stage branch_taken/branch_target are only\\nused locally before being redundantly flopped into EX/MEM.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current post-MDU core is Fmax-sensitive enough that small reductions in\\npipeline register width and hot-stage routing can still move Tang Nano 20K\\nfitness. Several metadata fields are carried after decode/execute but are not\\nconsumed by any later stage or by RVFI: LUI is already represented by\\nalu_op=ALU_LUI plus alu_src, and EX-stage branch_taken/branch_target are only\\nused locally before being redundantly flopped into EX/MEM.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Remove dead metadata from the pipeline bundles and the wiring that feeds it:\\ndrop ctrl_t.is_lui and the decoder/id-stage plumbing for it, and drop\\nex_mem_t.branch_taken plus ex_mem_t.branch_target and their EX-stage register\\nassignments. This should reduce flip-flops, mux inputs, and routing pressure\\nacross ID/EX and EX/MEM without changing instruction semantics, branch\\nredirect timing, memory behavior, or the nret=1 RVFI retirement interface.\\nBecause the change is pure metadata pruning, CPI should be unchanged while\\nmedian Fmax may improve modestly.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 2, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove unused ctrl_t.is_lui and dead ex_mem_t branch_taken/branch_target fields from the pipeline bundle definitions.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/decoder.sv\", \"description\": \"Drop the unused is_lui output and its assignments while preserving LUI legality, ALU_LUI select... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","time":{"start":1778663224502,"end":1778663224505}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b444d5462cd769a016a043f32c6308199a261bb257af1f841"}},"id":"prt_e2096df120014m9lQH4nmnANS7","sessionID":"ses_1df6a00f7ffegIolN9Kerr5CUi","messageID":"msg_e209652bf0010NKwMUGzpBs0Zi"}}
