{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778663294601,"sessionID":"ses_1df6a00f7ffegIolN9Kerr5CUi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ajObBqIDZt1TdZh6MblEFbTw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r4s0\n+title: \"Prune load writeback select bit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best bench core is already dominated by FPGA Fmax rather than\n+  large CPI opportunities, and the recent successful micro-opts both came\n+  from removing unnecessary reset or pipeline metadata. One remaining control\n+  bit, mem_to_reg, is redundant with mem_read: every legal load asserts both,\n+  and no non-load instruction should select the loaded-data path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg from the pipeline control bundle and use mem_read\n+  directly as the writeback-stage load-result selector. This eliminates one\n+  decoded control bit from the ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB payloads plus its\n+  decoder and ID-stage plumbing, without changing retirement timing, memory\n+  behavior, RVFI fields, or the nret=1 top-level interface. The expected win\n+  is modest but low-risk: slightly narrower pipeline registers and less\n+  routing/mux control on a core whose prior Fmax improved from similar\n+  metadata pruning.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the redundant ctrl_t.mem_to_reg field from the shared control bundle definition.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the mem_to_reg output and assignments; keep mem_read, reg_write, legality, and load width/sign controls unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove decoder mem_to_reg wiring and stop populating the eliminated control bit in ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Select load read_data using in.ctrl.mem_read instead of the removed mem_to_reg bit.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r4s0\n+title: \"Prune load writeback select bit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best bench core is already dominated by FPGA Fmax rather than\n+  large CPI opportunities, and the recent successful micro-opts both came\n+  from removing unnecessary reset or pipeline metadata. One remaining control\n+  bit, mem_to_reg, is redundant with mem_read: every legal load asserts both,\n+  and no non-load instruction should select the loaded-data path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg from the pipeline control bundle and use mem_read\n+  directly as the writeback-stage load-result selector. This eliminates one\n+  decoded control bit from the ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB payloads plus its\n+  decoder and ID-stage plumbing, without changing retirement timing, memory\n+  behavior, RVFI fields, or the nret=1 top-level interface. The expected win\n+  is modest but low-risk: slightly narrower pipeline registers and less\n+  routing/mux control on a core whose prior Fmax improved from similar\n+  metadata pruning.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the redundant ctrl_t.mem_to_reg field from the shared control bundle definition.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the mem_to_reg output and assignments; keep mem_read, reg_write, legality, and load width/sign controls unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove decoder mem_to_reg wiring and stop populating the eliminated control bit in ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Select load read_data using in.ctrl.mem_read instead of the removed mem_to_reg bit.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r4s0\n+title: \"Prune load writeback select bit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best bench core is already dominated by FPGA Fmax rather than\n+  large CPI opportunities, and the recent successful micro-opts both came\n+  from removing unnecessary reset or pipeline metadata. One remaining control\n+  bit, mem_to_reg, is redundant with mem_read: every legal load asserts both,\n+  and no non-load instruction should select the loaded-data path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg from the pipeline control bundle and use mem_read\n+  directly as the writeback-stage load-result selector. This eliminates one\n+  decoded control bit from the ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB payloads plus its\n+  decoder and ID-stage plumbing, without changing retirement timing, memory\n+  behavior, RVFI fields, or the nret=1 top-level interface. The expected win\n+  is modest but low-risk: slightly narrower pipeline registers and less\n+  routing/mux control on a core whose prior Fmax improved from similar\n+  metadata pruning.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the redundant ctrl_t.mem_to_reg field from the shared control bundle definition.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the mem_to_reg output and assignments; keep mem_read, reg_write, legality, and load width/sign controls unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove decoder mem_to_reg wiring and stop populating the eliminated control bit in ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Select load read_data using in.ctrl.mem_read instead of the removed mem_to_reg bit.\"\n","additions":30,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778663294598,"end":1778663294600}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0fcc3e1a8071e56d016a043f6363f08198bf41250b20a8fc66"}},"id":"prt_e20979ca8001R8jCSnzeHt3Cxx","sessionID":"ses_1df6a00f7ffegIolN9Kerr5CUi","messageID":"msg_e2097682e001qOxiZ47GEN7Yhp"}}
