{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778666704621,"sessionID":"ses_1df34bda8ffeBBsqjqFjT3Mfmt","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_OpXqGeKWsn3p8A5UWSleBqZf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Reset only pipeline valid bits\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core is Fmax-sensitive and the strongest micro-opt wins came\n+  from removing unnecessary reset fanout and dead pipeline metadata. The ID/EX,\n+  EX/MEM, and MEM/WB pipeline registers still reset entire wide packed structs,\n+  including RVFI data fields, operand values, immediates, memory data, and PC\n+  metadata that are ignored whenever valid is low. On the Tang Nano 20K this\n+  reset muxing and fanout can cost routing and LUT delay without improving\n+  architectural behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Change the pipeline stage reset style so reset explicitly clears the validity\n+  and side-effect control needed to prevent retirement, writes, memory requests,\n+  redirects, and traps, while leaving data-only fields as don't-care until a\n+  valid instruction overwrites them. Preserve the existing bubble behavior for\n+  flushes and MDU stalls by assigning zero payloads where the design relies on\n+  them, but avoid global reset of wide data members on every pipeline register.\n+\n+  This should reduce reset fanout and data-path muxing across the widest stage\n+  boundaries without changing CPI, RVFI order, memory ordering, or the nret=1\n+  top-level interface. It follows the proven regfile-reset lesson while avoiding\n+  prior failed control-bundle repacking and operand-source changes.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"On reset, clear only ID/EX valid and side-effect control bits needed for a safe bubble instead of resetting the whole packed payload; keep flush behavior as a full bubble.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"On reset, clear EX/MEM valid and side-effect control plus MDU bookkeeping while avoiding reset muxes on unused data-only EX/MEM fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"On reset, clear MEM/WB valid, write/memory/trap control, and store-buffer state while avoiding full reset of RVFI data fields that are ignored when valid is low.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Reset only pipeline valid bits\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core is Fmax-sensitive and the strongest micro-opt wins came\n+  from removing unnecessary reset fanout and dead pipeline metadata. The ID/EX,\n+  EX/MEM, and MEM/WB pipeline registers still reset entire wide packed structs,\n+  including RVFI data fields, operand values, immediates, memory data, and PC\n+  metadata that are ignored whenever valid is low. On the Tang Nano 20K this\n+  reset muxing and fanout can cost routing and LUT delay without improving\n+  architectural behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Change the pipeline stage reset style so reset explicitly clears the validity\n+  and side-effect control needed to prevent retirement, writes, memory requests,\n+  redirects, and traps, while leaving data-only fields as don't-care until a\n+  valid instruction overwrites them. Preserve the existing bubble behavior for\n+  flushes and MDU stalls by assigning zero payloads where the design relies on\n+  them, but avoid global reset of wide data members on every pipeline register.\n+\n+  This should reduce reset fanout and data-path muxing across the widest stage\n+  boundaries without changing CPI, RVFI order, memory ordering, or the nret=1\n+  top-level interface. It follows the proven regfile-reset lesson while avoiding\n+  prior failed control-bundle repacking and operand-source changes.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"On reset, clear only ID/EX valid and side-effect control bits needed for a safe bubble instead of resetting the whole packed payload; keep flush behavior as a full bubble.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"On reset, clear EX/MEM valid and side-effect control plus MDU bookkeeping while avoiding reset muxes on unused data-only EX/MEM fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"On reset, clear MEM/WB valid, write/memory/trap control, and store-buffer state while avoiding full reset of RVFI data fields that are ignored when valid is low.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/ben