{"type":"text","timestamp":1778668576983,"sessionID":"ses_1df17b467ffepM93Oap3ohTcIC","part":{"id":"prt_e20e89be6001wydZWELbeEg3pS","messageID":"msg_e20e87a49001IsbMsGTrhDVtAE","sessionID":"ses_1df17b467ffepM93Oap3ohTcIC","type":"text","text":"The prior micro-opt wins were narrow Fmax/routing reductions; broad control repacking and reset-style changes regressed. I’m going to propose a smaller micro-optimization: qualify forwarding comparisons with actual operand-use bits computed from the existing ID instruction, avoiding unnecessary rs2 comparator/mux activity for I-type/load/jump/upper-immediate instructions without changing RVFI source reporting.","time":{"start":1778668575718,"end":1778668576982},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0fc49acae6fcfaff016a04541f9cc08198b6bb5edccb78a463","phase":"commentary"}}}}
