{"type":"text","timestamp":1778668617589,"sessionID":"ses_1df17b467ffepM93Oap3ohTcIC","part":{"id":"prt_e20e9398e001df7GSr2eqYXsrC","messageID":"msg_e20e8aaab0010F16FeejyNJkX1","sessionID":"ses_1df17b467ffepM93Oap3ohTcIC","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a single-file MDU latency tweak: reduce multiply-family latency only, leaving division/remainder and the decoder/RVFI contract untouched.","time":{"start":1778668616078,"end":1778668617588},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c6bec9996ccbe82016a045447f960819a8401b0fce2f1ce7f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778668632495,"sessionID":"ses_1df17b467ffepM93Oap3ohTcIC","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_IyNg0SamwJxQZ7CBSvDULwG8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Shorten MDU multiply latency\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already moved RV32M operations out of the common ALU path,\n+  which improved Fmax substantially, but the MDU still assigns all multiply-family\n+  operations a two-cycle internal latency even though the product is computed and\n+  captured at launch. CoreMark uses some RV32M multiplies in its matrix/state code,\n+  so each avoidable MDU hold directly reduces counted cycles while leaving the hot\n+  RV32I EX path and front-end timing unchanged.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Change the real-hardware MDU latency table so MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU use\n+  the same one-cycle completion path already used by RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS mode,\n+  while keeping DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU at their existing long latency. The multiplier\n+  result is already formed combinationally before result_q is captured, so this is\n+  a control-latency reduction rather than adding new arithmetic hardware. It should\n+  improve CoreMark iterations/cycle on multiply instructions with little Fmax risk,\n+  and it does not affect memory ordering, fetch behavior, RVFI order, or nret=1 IO.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mdu.sv\n+    description: \"Set multiply-family MDU latency to one completion cycle while leaving divide/remainder latency and ALTOPS behavior unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/c