{"type":"text","timestamp":1778670677048,"sessionID":"ses_1def7f27dffe461ltPbRE8IdDF","part":{"id":"prt_e2108a79e001eWKJwmQRt4Wqqj","messageID":"msg_e21084a38001VwvQorsXs81uOl","sessionID":"ses_1def7f27dffe461ltPbRE8IdDF","type":"text","text":"The prior micro-opts show the best wins came from removing hot-path timing/routing, while branch prediction, load-result bypass, and wider control repacking regressed. I’m going to propose a narrow EX-stage control optimization: decode an explicit MDU-op bit so the common EX path no longer builds an eight-way `alu_op` comparator just to decide whether to stall for RV32M.","time":{"start":1778670675870,"end":1778670677046},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0bdffbc311a1256b016a045c53c1f4819bb7f66346439e9e6e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
