{"type":"text","timestamp":1778670685393,"sessionID":"ses_1def7f27dffe461ltPbRE8IdDF","part":{"id":"prt_e2108c6f0001HDHyvQpe8UMRze","messageID":"msg_e2108bbe0001ipcYcwKRE3n0du","sessionID":"ses_1def7f27dffe461ltPbRE8IdDF","type":"text","text":"I’ll write the hypothesis YAML now, scoped only to `cores/bench` and using schema-valid short paths in `changes`.","time":{"start":1778670683888,"end":1778670685392},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c16da4073e7b588016a045c5bcd04819a8cc9e4c2ba3b292c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778670706944,"sessionID":"ses_1def7f27dffe461ltPbRE8IdDF","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_8kOEBhK1xfzJfW1c5PfW7wUl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r9s0\n+title: \"Decode explicit MDU op bit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent bench results show the current core is more sensitive to Tang Nano 20K\n+  Fmax and routing than to speculative CPI tweaks. The EX stage still detects\n+  RV32M operations by comparing the 5-bit ALU opcode against all eight MDU\n+  encodings, then uses that result to drive the MDU start, EX busy/stall, result\n+  mux, and RVFI operand capture paths. That decode sits in the hot execute\n+  control cone even though the decoder already knows exactly when funct7=1 marks\n+  an M-extension instruction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single decoded control bit, for example ctrl_t.is_mdu, asserted only for\n+  legal RV32M OP instructions in rtl/decoder.sv and carried through ID/EX. Use\n+  this bit in rtl/ex_stage.sv instead of the current eight-way alu_op equality\n+  chain when generating is_m_op, mdu_start, ex_busy, exec_result selection, and\n+  MDU operand capture selection.\n+\n+  This intentionally adds one ID/EX control bit but removes repeated ALU-op\n+  comparisons from the common EX-stage control path. It does not alter MDU\n+  arithmetic, latencies, branch/fetch behavior, memory ordering, RVFI retirement,\n+  or the nret=1 IO contract. The expected gain is a small median Fmax lift from\n+  simpler EX control with unchanged CoreMark CPI.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add an is_mdu control bit to ctrl_t so decode can mark legal RV32M operations explicitly.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Assert the new is_mdu bit only in the validated funct7=0x01 OP cases while preserving decoder illegal defaults.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the decoder's is_mdu output into the ID/EX control bundle without changing other decoded controls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the eight-way ALU-op comparison used for is_m_op with the decoded control bit, keeping MDU start/busy/result behavior unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r9s0\n+title: \"Decode explicit MDU op bit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent bench results show the current core is more sensitive to Tang Nano 20K\n+  Fmax and routing than to speculative CPI tweaks. The EX stage still detects\n+  RV32M operations by comparing the 5-bit ALU opcode against all eight MDU\n+  encodings, then uses that result to drive the MDU start, EX busy/stall, result\n+  mux, and RVFI operand capture paths. That decode sits in the hot execute\n+  control cone even though the decoder already knows exactly when funct7=1 marks\n+  an M-extension instruction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single decoded control bit, for example ctrl_t.is_mdu, asserted only for\n+  legal RV32M OP instructions in rtl/decoder.sv and carried through ID/EX. Use\n+  this bit in rtl/ex_stage.sv instead of the current eight-way alu_op equality\n+  chain when generating is_m_op, mdu_start, ex_busy, exec_result selection, and\n+  MDU operand capture selection.\n+\n+  This intentionally adds one ID/EX control bit but removes repeated ALU-op\n+  comparisons from the common EX-stage control path. It does not alter MDU\n+  arithmetic, latencies, branch/fetch behavior, memory ordering, RVFI retirement,\n+  or the nret=1 IO contract. The expected gain is a small median Fmax lift from\n+  simpler EX control with unchanged CoreMark CPI.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add an is_mdu control bit to ctrl_t so decode can mark legal RV32M operations explicitly.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Assert the new is_mdu bit only in the validated funct7=0x01 OP cases while preserving decoder illegal defaults.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the decoder's is_mdu output into the ID/EX control bundle without changing other decoded controls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the eight-way ALU-op comparison used for is_m_op with the decoded control bit, keeping MDU start/busy/result behavior unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\