{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778671920589,"sessionID":"ses_1dee5adf2fferRNpMbi4QoWQW0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_1Z6TcOK5PCsDKF30fjpm8bKd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r10s1\n+title: \"Split EX common add path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent structural wins came from removing common-path pressure in the back end,\n+  while front-end replay, prediction, and deeper queues repeatedly regressed on\n+  Tang Nano 20K. The current EX stage still routes every ordinary register result\n+  through the general ALU case mux, which includes compare and variable-shift\n+  alternatives even for CoreMark's common add, immediate-add, load/store address,\n+  AUIPC, and jump-link paths.\n+\n+  A narrow EX-stage datapath split can reduce the hot forwarding-to-EX/MEM timing\n+  cone without changing fetch, branch prediction, memory ordering, MDU behavior,\n+  or the nret=1 RVFI retirement contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure ex_stage so common add-like operations use a dedicated fast result\n+  path: compute add/sub/address/AUIPC/JAL link results separately from the general\n+  shift/logic/compare ALU cone, then select the small fast result for ALU_ADD,\n+  ALU_SUB, ALU_LUI, AUIPC, load/store address generation, and JAL/JALR link writes.\n+  Keep the existing alu.sv for less-common logic, compare, and shift operations,\n+  and preserve the multicycle MDU launch/commit path exactly as today.\n+\n+  This should improve Fmax by keeping CoreMark's dominant integer/address path out\n+  of the wide ALU operation mux while adding only local EX-stage muxing. CPI should\n+  be unchanged, and correctness risk is limited because all instructions still\n+  retire through the same EX/MEM and MEM/WB structures with the same RVFI fields.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated fast EX result path for add/sub/address/AUIPC/JAL link operations and select it before falling back to the existing ALU or MDU result.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Optionally narrow the general ALU to the remaining logic, compare, and shift operations once the common add-like path is handled directly in ex_stage.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r10s1\n+title: \"Split EX common add path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent structural wins came from removing common-path pressure in the back end,\n+  while front-end replay, prediction, and deeper queues repeatedly regressed on\n+  Tang Nano 20K. The current EX stage still routes every ordinary register result\n+  through the general ALU case mux, which includes compare and variable-shift\n+  alternatives even for CoreMark's common add, immediate-add, load/store address,\n+  AUIPC, and jump-link paths.\n+\n+  A narrow EX-stage datapath split can reduce the hot forwarding-to-EX/MEM timing\n+  cone without changing fetch, branch prediction, memory ordering, MDU behavior,\n+  or the nret=1 RVFI retirement contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure ex_stage so common add-like operations use a dedicated fast result\n+  path: compute add/sub/address/AUIPC/JAL link results separately from the general\n+  shift/logic/compare ALU cone, then select the small fast result for ALU_ADD,\n+  ALU_SUB, ALU_LUI, AUIPC, load/store address generation, and JAL/JALR link writes.\n+  Keep the existing alu.sv for less-common logic, compare, and shift operations,\n+  and preserve the multicycle MDU launch/commit path exactly as today.\n+\n+  This should improve Fmax by keeping CoreMark's dominant integer/address path out\n+  of the wide ALU operation mux while adding only local EX-stage muxing. CPI should\n+  be unchanged, and correctness risk is limited because all instructions still\n+  retire through the same EX/MEM and MEM/WB structures with the same RVFI fields.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated fast EX result path for add/sub/address/AUIPC/JAL link operations and select it before falling back to the existing ALU or MDU result.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Optionally narrow the general ALU to the remaining logic, compare, and shift operations once the common add-like path is handled directly in ex_stage.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_