path out\n24:   of the wide ALU operation mux while adding only local EX-stage muxing. CPI should\n25:   be unchanged, and correctness risk is limited because all instructions still\n26:   retire through the same EX/MEM and MEM/WB structures with the same RVFI fields.\n27: expected_impact:\n28:   fitness_delta_pct: 4\n29:   confidence: medium\n30: changes:\n31:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n32:     description: \"Add a dedicated fast EX result path for add/sub/address/AUIPC/JAL link operations and select it before falling back to the existing ALU or MDU result.\"\n33:   - file: rtl/alu.sv\n34:     description: \"Optionally narrow the general ALU to the remaining logic, compare, and shift operations once the common add-like path is handled directly in ex_stage.\"\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-002-r10s1\ntitle: \"Split EX common add path\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  Recent structural wins came from removing common-path pressure in the back end,\n  while front-end replay, prediction, and deeper queues repeatedly regressed on\n  Tang Nano 20K. The current EX stage still routes every ordinary register result\n  through the general ALU case mux, which includes compare and variable-shift\n  alternatives even for CoreMark's common add, immediate-add, load/store address,\n  AUIPC, and jump-link paths.\n\n  A narrow EX-stage datapath split can reduce the hot forwarding-to-EX/MEM timing\n  cone without changing fetch, branch prediction, memory ordering, MDU behavior,\n  or the nret=1 RVFI retirement contract.\nhypothesis: |\n  Restructure ex_stage so common add-like operations use a dedicated fast result\n  path: compute add/sub/address/AUIPC/JAL link results separately from the general\n  shift/logic/compare ALU cone, then select the small fast result for ALU_ADD,\n  ALU_SUB, ALU_LUI, AUIPC, load/store address generation, and JAL/JALR link writes.\n  Keep the existing alu.sv for less-common logic, compare, and shift operations,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r10s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778671926975,"end":1778671926982}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_091547e4efb57afb016a04613663b88198b6dae3a7dbf4ad67"}},"id":"prt_e211bbcf0001bpcr0foyTncQmM","sessionID":"ses_1dee5adf2fferRNpMbi4QoWQW0","messageID":"msg_e211ba65e001E2r3RXiVnC1Der"}}
