{"type":"text","timestamp":1778672652258,"sessionID":"ses_1deda830effepLLiklnjw5dkNk","part":{"id":"prt_e2126ccb1001nSWgzup8CH3Hip","messageID":"msg_e21263291001GUBmOm1BvqFUK4","sessionID":"ses_1deda830effepLLiklnjw5dkNk","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a narrow back-end structural change: store-buffer load forwarding for exact/covered hits, preserving the single-entry buffer and stalling all non-forwardable memory ops behind it.","time":{"start":1778672651441,"end":1778672652257},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_059db9ce3d7610d2016a04640b51148199a31ef511ace5a90e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778672673014,"sessionID":"ses_1deda830effepLLiklnjw5dkNk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_FHPDl1fEXoClJg3csfUVEMSY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Forward loads from store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best structural win is the one-entry posted store buffer, which\n+  lets isolated stores retire while a stalled dmem write drains. Its remaining\n+  conservative rule is that every younger memory operation stalls behind any\n+  buffered store, even when the younger load reads bytes wholly covered by that\n+  pending store. CoreMark stack and struct traffic can contain store-then-load\n+  pairs where random dmem backpressure currently turns a safe forwarding case\n+  into a full pipeline stall.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add store-buffer load forwarding inside the existing MEM-stage decoupling\n+  structure. When the posted store buffer is full and the instruction in EX/MEM\n+  is a valid, aligned load to the same word with a byte mask fully covered by\n+  the buffered store mask, synthesize the load word from the buffered replicated\n+  store data, let the load retire normally, and do not assert a dmem read for\n+  that forwarded access. Keep all nonmatching, partially covered, misaligned,\n+  and store-following-memory cases stalled behind the buffer exactly as today.\n+\n+  This preserves precise in-order retirement, RVFI memory reporting, and the\n+  nret=1 top-level contract while improving the useful decoupling of the proven\n+  one-entry store buffer. The change stays entirely in the back end, avoiding\n+  the front-end replay and prediction paths that repeatedly regressed.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect same-word store-buffer hits for aligned loads whose requested byte mask is fully covered, return buffered data as load data, suppress dmem_ren for forwarded loads, and report correct RVFI rdata/rmask.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Allow a current EX/MEM load to proceed while the posted store buffer is full only when mem_stage reports that the load can be fully forwarded from the buffer.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the store-buffer load-forwarding qualification from mem_stage into hazard_unit without changing the nret=1 IO shape.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Forward loads from store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best structural win is the one-entry posted store buffer, which\n+  lets isolated stores retire while a stalled dmem write drains. Its remaining\n+  conservative rule is that every younger memory operation stalls behind any\n+  buffered store, even when the younger load reads bytes wholly covered by that\n+  pending store. CoreMark stack and struct traffic can contain store-then-load\n+  pairs where random dmem backpressure currently turns a safe forwarding case\n+  into a full pipeline stall.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add store-buffer load forwarding inside the existing MEM-stage decoupling\n+  structure. When the posted store buffer is full and the instruction in EX/MEM\n+  is a valid, aligned load to the same word with a byte mask fully covered by\n+  the buffered store mask, synthesize the load word from the buffered replicated\n+  store data, let the load retire normally, and do not assert a dmem read for\n+  that forwarded access. Keep all nonmatching, partially covered, misaligned,\n+  and store-following-memory cases stalled behind the buffer exactly as today.\n+\n+  This preserves precise in-order retirement, RVFI memory reporting, and the\n+  nret=1 top-level contract while improving the useful decoupling of the proven\n+  one-entry store buffer. The change stays entirely in the back end, avoiding\n+  the front-end replay and prediction paths that repeatedly regressed.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect same-word store-buffer hits for aligned loads whose requested byte mask is fully covered, return buffered data as load data, suppress dmem_ren for forwarded loads, and report correct RVFI rdata/rmask.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Allow a current EX/MEM load to proceed while the posted store buffer is full only when mem_stage reports that the load can be fully forwarded from the buffer.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the store-buffer load-forwarding qualification from mem_stage into hazard_unit without changing the nret=1 IO shape.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n==================================================================