ffer hits for aligned loads whose requested byte mask is fully covered, return buffered data as load data, suppress dmem_ren for forwarded loads, and report correct RVFI rdata/rmask.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Allow a current EX/MEM load to proceed while the posted store buffer is full only when mem_stage reports that the load can be fully forwarded from the buffer.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the store-buffer load-forwarding qualification from mem_stage into hazard_unit without changing the nret=1 IO shape.\"\n","additions":34,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778672673010,"end":1778672673013}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_059db9ce3d7610d2016a04640c1d808199b050f035a562ea91"}},"id":"prt_e2126cfe2002MvJihAZ7s1ijg8","sessionID":"ses_1deda830effepLLiklnjw5dkNk","messageID":"msg_e21263291001GUBmOm1BvqFUK4"}}
