{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778673539496,"sessionID":"ses_1decbe5d7ffe9Ar2cwzAU0pEo5","part":{"id":"prt_e213459a5001wioMqjERx5MG4o","messageID":"msg_e2134544c001xZRJd7TbJbS8vx","sessionID":"ses_1decbe5d7ffe9Ar2cwzAU0pEo5","snapshot":"42653fa39905d06362a6fd015602721f9365bb1e","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778673544276,"sessionID":"ses_1decbe5d7ffe9Ar2cwzAU0pEo5","part":{"id":"prt_e21346716001Bw9oYghhHM5R0Y","messageID":"msg_e2134544c001xZRJd7TbJbS8vx","sessionID":"ses_1decbe5d7ffe9Ar2cwzAU0pEo5","type":"text","text":"The history confirms structural wins only came from back-end decoupling and writeback retiming; front-end/predictor/replay and wider queues have repeatedly regressed. I’m going to propose a narrow structural retiming that removes MEM/WB control and address fanout from the forwarding path rather than adding new speculation or buffering.","time":{"start":1778673542934,"end":1778673544275},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0916fad972539ea8016a046786cf188198ac421756c38104ce","phase":"commentary"}}}}
