{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778673586311,"sessionID":"ses_1decbe5d7ffe9Ar2cwzAU0pEo5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_1CtuFOnQdOsZPwNdSY4ukFKr","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Add narrow forwarding sideband\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already improved by registering final writeback data,\n+  but the EX forwarding decision still reaches back into the wide MEM/WB and\n+  EX/MEM pipeline records for rd and reg_write metadata. Those packed records\n+  also feed RVFI, memory reporting, and hold-on-dmem-stall behavior, so their\n+  hot fields can inherit unnecessary fanout and routing pressure on Tang Nano\n+  20K.\n+\n+  Prior structural wins came from narrow back-end decoupling and retiming,\n+  while front-end replay, prediction, deeper queues, and new same-cycle load\n+  paths repeatedly regressed. A dedicated forwarding sideband keeps the proven\n+  pipeline behavior but gives synthesis a smaller set of signals for the EX\n+  operand mux control cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add explicit narrow forwarding sideband signals for the two producer stages:\n+  exmem_fwd_en/rd/data and memwb_fwd_en/rd/data. Drive them from the existing\n+  registered stage outputs, preserving the current semantics that MEM/WB may\n+  remain forwardable during a dmem hold even when valid is cleared to avoid a\n+  double retirement. Then make forward_unit consume only these sideband fields\n+  instead of the wide ex_mem_t and mem_wb_t control/data records.\n+\n+  This should reduce fanout from ctrl_t.reg_write, rd, and wb_data fields that\n+  currently serve forwarding, writeback, RVFI, and hazard-related paths. CPI,\n+  RVFI order, memory ordering, MDU behavior, store-buffer behavior, and the\n+  nret=1 top-level interface remain unchanged; the intended benefit is a small\n+  Fmax lift from cleaner placement and a narrower EX operand-control path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Create narrow EX/MEM and MEM/WB forwarding sideband wires and connect forward_unit/ex_stage through them without changing the nret=1 IO contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Consume forward-enable, rd, and data sideband metadata rather than broad pipeline control records, preserving EX/MEM priority over MEM/WB.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Optionally expose or document the forwardable writeback enable semantics separately from architectural valid-gated regfile writes.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Add narrow forwarding sideband\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already improved by registering final writeback data,\n+  but the EX forwarding decision still reaches back into the wide MEM/WB and\n+  EX/MEM pipeline records for rd and reg_write metadata. Those packed records\n+  also feed RVFI, memory reporting, and hold-on-dmem-stall behavior, so their\n+  hot fields can inherit unnecessary fanout and routing pressure on Tang Nano\n+  20K.\n+\n+  Prior structural wins came from narrow back-end decoupling and retiming,\n+  while front-end replay, prediction, deeper queues, and new same-cycle load\n+  paths repeatedly regressed. A dedicated forwarding sideband keeps the proven\n+  pipeline behavior but gives synthesis a smaller set of signals for the EX\n+  operand mux control cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add explicit narrow forwarding sideband signals for the two producer stages:\n+  exmem_fwd_en/rd/data and memwb_fwd_en/rd/data. Drive them from the existing\n+  registered stage outputs, preserving the current semantics that MEM/WB may\n+  remain forwardable during a dmem hold even when valid is cleared to avoid a\n+  double retirement. Then make forward_unit consume only these sideband fields\n+  instead of the wide ex_mem_t and mem_wb_t control/data records.\n+\n+  This should reduce fanout from ctrl_t.reg_write, rd, and wb_data fields that\n+  currently serve forwarding, writeback, RVFI, and hazard-related paths. CPI,\n+  RVFI order, memory ordering, MDU behavior, store-buffer behavior, and the\n+  nret=1 top-level interface remain unchanged; the intended benefit is a small\n+  Fmax lift from cleaner placement and a narrower EX operand-control path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Create narrow EX/MEM and MEM/WB forwarding sideband wires and connect forward_unit/ex_stage through them without changing the nret=1 IO contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Consume forward-enable, rd, and data sideband metadata rather than broad pipeline control records, preserving EX/MEM priority over MEM/WB.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Optionally expose or document the forwardable writeback enable semantics separately from architectural valid-gated regfile writes.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_mediu