{"type":"text","timestamp":1778676452402,"sessionID":"ses_1dea05250ffekoes52vAfxWS2A","part":{"id":"prt_e2160ca23001xR3B03BbihAmKS","messageID":"msg_e215fd84e001GtOm4Ta40gtfvw","sessionID":"ses_1dea05250ffekoes52vAfxWS2A","type":"text","text":"The prior structural wins are concentrated in back-end decoupling and narrow retiming; front-end prediction/replay and deeper queues repeatedly regressed. I’m writing a one-entry store-buffer throughput hypothesis that preserves the existing buffer depth but lets it drain and accept the next store in the same cycle.","time":{"start":1778676451875,"end":1778676452400},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_058ff8e510388682016a0472e3c444819b8024d0d3023c677b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778676474107,"sessionID":"ses_1dea05250ffekoes52vAfxWS2A","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_GJ24EJGQZeJ0PUnNLqP5LfjH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Store buffer drain refill\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The only durable CPI-oriented structural improvement in this core has been\n+  the one-entry posted store buffer. It lets an isolated store retire while a\n+  stalled dmem write drains, but it still creates a full bubble when the buffer\n+  becomes ready to drain in the same cycle that the next store is waiting in\n+  EX/MEM. Deepening the buffer to two entries failed placement, so the next\n+  promising structural angle is to improve throughput of the existing single\n+  entry rather than add queue depth or front-end speculation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Teach the one-entry posted store buffer to perform a same-cycle drain/refill:\n+  when an older buffered store owns the dmem port and io_dmemReady is high,\n+  allow a younger valid aligned store already in EX/MEM to retire and replace\n+  the buffer entry, while the old entry is the one driven to memory that cycle.\n+  Younger loads and non-store memory operations should still stall behind any\n+  buffered store because the single dmem port cannot service them during the\n+  drain cycle, and non-memory instructions keep the existing behavior.\n+\n+  This keeps the proven one-entry structure and precise store ordering, but\n+  removes a recurrent bubble for store bursts under random dmem backpressure.\n+  It avoids the failed two-entry FIFO data movement and does not touch fetch,\n+  branch prediction, MDU behavior, RVFI ordering, or the nret=1 top-level IO.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the posted store buffer state machine so a ready buffered store can drain to dmem while the current aligned store captures into the same single entry and retires once.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Distinguish buffered-store blocking for loads/younger memory ops from the safe same-cycle drain/refill case for a younger store.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire any refined store-buffer status signal between mem_stage and hazard_unit without changing the nret=1 top-level port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Store buffer drain refill\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The only durable CPI-oriented structural improvement in this core has been\n+  the one-entry posted store buffer. It lets an isolated store retire while a\n+  stalled dmem write drains, but it still creates a full bubble when the buffer\n+  becomes ready to drain in the same cycle that the next store is waiting in\n+  EX/MEM. Deepening the buffer to two entries failed placement, so the next\n+  promising structural angle is to improve throughput of the existing single\n+  entry rather than add queue depth or front-end speculation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Teach the one-entry posted store buffer to perform a same-cycle drain/refill:\n+  when an older buffered store owns the dmem port and io_dmemReady is high,\n+  allow a younger valid aligned store already in EX/MEM to retire and replace\n+  the buffer entry, while the old entry is the one driven to memory that cycle.\n+  Younger loads and non-store memory operations should still stall behind any\n+  buffered store because the single dmem port cannot service them during the\n+  drain cycle, and non-memory instructions keep the existing behavior.\n+\n+  This keeps the proven one-entry structure and precise store ordering, but\n+  removes a recurrent bubble for store bursts under random dmem backpressure.\n+  It avoids the failed two-entry FIFO data movement and does not touch fetch,\n+  branch prediction, MDU behavior, RVFI ordering, or the nret=1 top-level IO.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the posted store buffer state machine so a ready buffered store can drain to dmem while the current aligned store captures into the same single entry and retires once.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Distinguish buffered-store blocking for loads/younger memory ops from the safe same-cycle drain/refill case for a younger store.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire any refined store-buffer status signal between mem_stage and hazard_unit without changing the nret=1 top-level port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n===============================================================