{"type":"text","timestamp":1778657248361,"sessionID":"ses_1dfc49df4ffeEuRqDg4eIwxR0r","part":{"id":"prt_e203bb81a001k14JTjjveXE9jz","messageID":"msg_e203b9b89001xYRf35XNVOkSGv","sessionID":"ses_1dfc49df4ffeEuRqDg4eIwxR0r","type":"text","text":"No `LESSONS.md` exists and the log only contains the baseline retest, so there are no prior structural results to avoid. The strongest structural hypothesis is to reduce branch/jump penalty by moving redirect resolution from EX into ID for simple branches/jumps, since CoreMark has frequent loop branches and calls under random fetch stalls.","time":{"start":1778657245210,"end":1778657248359},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07317efb10c030ea016a0427dd19388198bb984ca85589f511","phase":"commentary"}}}}
