{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778657285089,"sessionID":"ses_1dfc49df4ffeEuRqDg4eIwxR0r","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_pvnrYBkBoSEBETyYXXoRfVfA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Resolve branches in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves every branch and jump in EX, so each\n+  taken redirect flushes two younger instructions. CoreMark spends many cycles\n+  in tight counted loops and function-call-heavy list/state code, making taken\n+  control transfers a direct CPI cost. Reducing the redirect penalty by one\n+  stage should improve iterations per cycle without changing the nret=1 RVFI\n+  contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an ID-stage early redirect path for conditional branches, JAL, and JALR\n+  when their operands are already available from the regfile or safe same-cycle\n+  bypasses. The ID stage can compute immediates, branch comparisons, and jump\n+  targets one cycle earlier than EX; when it redirects, IF emits a bubble and\n+  ID/EX captures a bubble so the control-transfer instruction still retires\n+  through the normal pipeline with correct RVFI pc_wdata. Cases needing an\n+  unavailable producer, especially load-use and EX/MEM load results, fall back\n+  to the existing EX resolution path for correctness.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire an early ID redirect signal into IF and hazard control while preserving the existing EX redirect fallback and single-channel RVFI retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute branch and jump targets in ID, compare available operands with WB bypassing, emit an early redirect, and carry the resolved pc_next metadata into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Honor ID-resolved control transfers so EX does not issue a duplicate redirect, while retaining misalignment trap handling and fallback resolution.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal ID/EX metadata fields for whether a control transfer was resolved early and what next PC should be reported to RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Prioritize the early redirect flush and preserve stall behavior for unsafe branch operand dependencies.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Resolve branches in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves every branch and jump in EX, so each\n+  taken redirect flushes two younger instructions. CoreMark spends many cycles\n+  in tight counted loops and function-call-heavy list/state code, making taken\n+  control transfers a direct CPI cost. Reducing the redirect penalty by one\n+  stage should improve iterations per cycle without changing the nret=1 RVFI\n+  contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an ID-stage early redirect path for conditional branches, JAL, and JALR\n+  when their operands are already available from the regfile or safe same-cycle\n+  bypasses. The ID stage can compute immediates, branch comparisons, and jump\n+  targets one cycle earlier than EX; when it redirects, IF emits a bubble and\n+  ID/EX captures a bubble so the control-transfer instruction still retires\n+  through the normal pipeline with correct RVFI pc_wdata. Cases needing an\n+  unavailable producer, especially load-use and EX/MEM load results, fall back\n+  to the existing EX resolution path for correctness.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire an early ID redirect signal into IF and hazard control while preserving the existing EX redirect fallback and single-channel RVFI retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute branch and jump targets in ID, compare available operands with WB bypassing, emit an early redirect, and carry the resolved pc_next metadata into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Honor ID-resolved control transfers so EX does not issue a duplicate redirect, while retaining misalignment trap handling and fallback resolution.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal ID/EX metadata fields for whether a control transfer was resolved early and what next PC should be reported to RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Prioritize the early redirect flush and preserve stall behavior for unsafe branch operand dependencies.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-re