{"type":"text","timestamp":1778659565697,"sessionID":"ses_1dfa17494ffe6uTyrmdxXbFkDg","part":{"id":"prt_e205f1ed4001z2xHhBwQVxm5hQ","messageID":"msg_e205edfdf001r0z0WwbPk6XP1S","sessionID":"ses_1dfa17494ffe6uTyrmdxXbFkDg","type":"text","text":"The only prior structural attempt was early branch resolution in ID, and the lesson is that moving control resolution earlier added cost without enough bypass coverage. I’m choosing a narrower structural change aimed at Fmax and CPI neutrality: split the heavy combinational M-extension ALU path out of the normal EX critical path with a small iterative multicycle unit and pipeline stalls only for M ops.","time":{"start":1778659565268,"end":1778659565696},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f4b64e0c28a9817016a0430ed29f88198ba384191bcfc5dd9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
