{"type":"text","timestamp":1778663215004,"sessionID":"ses_1df6a0176ffevdE76ufkR1w8iY","part":{"id":"prt_e2096c919001d8OVNv0JAXKgpM","messageID":"msg_e209648bd001E7DtHBgg8vo7gu","sessionID":"ses_1df6a0176ffevdE76ufkR1w8iY","type":"text","text":"The prior structural wins came from removing M-extension hardware from the common EX path; the structural regressions were front-end speculation/buffering. I’m going to propose a non-speculative pipeline retiming: add a real IF/ID register to cut the current fetch-to-decode combinational path while preserving EX-authoritative redirects.","time":{"start":1778663213337,"end":1778663215003},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ff6cc07bde3f448016a043f2d3b388198971aa261f6015274","phase":"commentary"}}}}
