{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778663276686,"sessionID":"ses_1df6a0176ffevdE76ufkR1w8iY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_oLRXOcomJ21ioi8un2WWPvym","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Register the IF ID boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end has no real IF/ID pipeline register: imem_data, PC,\n+  decode, immediate generation, register-file address selection, and the ID/EX\n+  capture all sit in one cycle. After the successful MDU split and metadata\n+  pruning, the remaining Tang Nano 20K fitness is likely limited by routing and\n+  long stage boundaries rather than by CoreMark CPI alone.\n+\n+  Prior structural and predictor attempts that added front-end speculation or\n+  replay state regressed because they put new work on the fetch next-PC path.\n+  A plain IF/ID register is a narrower structural retiming that does not try to\n+  predict control flow; it simply cuts the fetch-to-decode path and lets the PC\n+  and instruction memory interface settle before decode consumes the word.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert the current combinational IF/ID bundle into a registered pipeline\n+  boundary owned by if_stage. The IF stage should capture pc, instr, and valid\n+  when imemReady is high and decode can advance; hold the registered bundle\n+  during load-use, dmem, and MDU stalls; and flush it on redirects or invalid\n+  instruction-fetch cycles. ID then decodes only the registered instruction,\n+  preserving the existing ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, forwarding, RVFI order, and\n+  nret=1 retirement behavior.\n+\n+  This retiming should shorten the critical path from instruction memory into\n+  decode/regfile/ID-EX control, improving Fmax without adding predictor muxes or\n+  branch-immediate decode to the fetch next-PC path. The CPI cost should be\n+  limited to pipeline fill and the existing redirect flush semantics; CoreMark's\n+  bracketed region is long enough that a modest Fmax gain should dominate.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a real IF/ID register for pc, instr, and valid; hold it on pipeline stalls and flush it on redirects or failed instruction fetches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust stall and flush semantics so the registered IF/ID boundary is held, bubbled, or cleared coherently under load-use, bus stalls, MDU busy, and redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the registered IF/ID control through the existing pipeline without changing the nret=1 RVFI port set or retirement boundary.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep ID decode behavior unchanged while consuming the newly registered IF/ID payload rather than a combinational fetch bundle.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Register the IF ID boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end has no real IF/ID pipeline register: imem_data, PC,\n+  decode, immediate generation, register-file address selection, and the ID/EX\n+  capture all sit in one cycle. After the successful MDU split and metadata\n+  pruning, the remaining Tang Nano 20K fitness is likely limited by routing and\n+  long stage boundaries rather than by CoreMark CPI alone.\n+\n+  Prior structural and predictor attempts that added front-end speculation or\n+  replay state regressed because they put new work on the fetch next-PC path.\n+  A plain IF/ID register is a narrower structural retiming that does not try to\n+  predict control flow; it simply cuts the fetch-to-decode path and lets the PC\n+  and instruction memory interface settle before decode consumes the word.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert the current combinational IF/ID bundle into a registered pipeline\n+  boundary owned by if_stage. The IF stage should capture pc, instr, and valid\n+  when imemReady is high and decode can advance; hold the registered bundle\n+  during load-use, dmem, and MDU stalls; and flush it on redirects or invalid\n+  instruction-fetch cycles. ID then decodes only the registered instruction,\n+  preserving the existing ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, forwarding, RVFI order, and\n+  nret=1 retirement behavior.\n+\n+  This retiming should shorten the critical path from instruction memory into\n+  decode/regfile/ID-EX control, improving Fmax without adding predictor muxes or\n+  branch-immediate decode to the fetch next-PC path. The CPI cost should be\n+  limited to pipeline fill and the existing redirect flush semantics; CoreMark's\n+  bracketed region is long enough that a modest Fmax gain should dominate.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a real IF/ID register for pc, instr, and valid; hold it on pipeline stalls and flush it on redirects or failed instruction fetches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust stall and flush semantics so the registered IF/ID boundary is held, bubbled, or cleared coherently under load-use, bus stalls, MDU busy, and redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the registered IF/ID control through the existing pipeline without changing the nret=1 RVFI port set or retirement boundary.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep ID decode behavior unchanged while consuming the newly registered IF/ID payload rather than a combinational fetch bundle.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Register the IF ID boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end has no real IF/ID pipeline register: imem_data, PC,\n+  decode, immediate generation, register-file address selection, and the ID/EX\n+  capture all sit in one cycle. After the successful MDU split and metadata\n+  pruning, the remaining Tang Nano 20K fitness is likely limited by routing and\n+  long stage boundaries rather than by CoreMark CPI alone.\n+\n+  Prior structural and predictor attempts that added front-end speculation or\n+  replay state regressed because they put new work on the fetch next-PC path.\n+  A plain IF/ID register is a narrower structural retiming that does not try to\n+  predict control flow; it simply cuts the fetch-to-decode path and lets the PC\n+  and instruction memory interface settle before decode consumes the word.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert the current combinational IF/ID bundle into a registered pipeline\n+  boundary owned by if_stage. The IF stage should capture pc, instr, and valid\n+  when imemReady is high and decode can advance; hold the registered bundle\n+  during load-use, dmem, and MDU stalls; and flush it on redirects or invalid\n+  instruction-fetch cycles. ID then decodes only the registered instruction,\n+  preserving the existing ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, forwarding, RVFI order, and\n+  nret=1 retirement behavior.\n+\n+  This retiming should shorten the critical path from instruction memory into\n+  decode/regfile/ID-EX control, improving Fmax without adding predictor muxes or\n+  branch-immediate decode to the fetch next-PC path. The CPI cost should be\n+  limited to pipeline fill and the existing redirect flush semantics; CoreMark's\n+  bracketed region is long enough that a modest Fmax gain should dominate.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a real IF/ID register for pc, instr, and valid; hold it on pipeline stalls and flush it on redirects or failed instruction fetches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust stall and flush semantics so the registered IF/ID boundary is held, bubbled, or cleared coherently under load-use, bus stalls, MDU busy, and redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the registered IF/ID control through the existing pipeline without changing the nret=1 RVFI port set or retirement boundary.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep ID decode behavior unchanged while consuming the newly registered IF/ID payload rather than a combinational fetch bundle.\"\n","additions":41,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experim