{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778663291124,"sessionID":"ses_1df6a0176ffevdE76ufkR1w8iY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_twlG3a23oMX0PZSLemjCP0pW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n2: title: \"Register the IF ID boundary\"\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current front end has no real IF/ID pipeline register: imem_data, PC,\n6:   decode, immediate generation, register-file address selection, and the ID/EX\n7:   capture all sit in one cycle. After the successful MDU split and metadata\n8:   pruning, the remaining Tang Nano 20K fitness is likely limited by routing and\n9:   long stage boundaries rather than by CoreMark CPI alone.\n10: \n11:   Prior structural and predictor attempts that added front-end speculation or\n12:   replay state regressed because they put new work on the fetch next-PC path.\n13:   A plain IF/ID register is a narrower structural retiming that does not try to\n14:   predict control flow; it simply cuts the fetch-to-decode path and lets the PC\n15:   and instruction memory interface settle before decode consumes the word.\n16: hypothesis: |\n17:   Convert the current combinational IF/ID bundle into a registered pipeline\n18:   boundary owned by if_stage. The IF stage should capture pc, instr, and valid\n19:   when imemReady is high and decode can advance; hold the registered bundle\n20:   during load-use, dmem, and MDU stalls; and flush it on redirects or invalid\n21:   instruction-fetch cycles. ID then decodes only the registered instruction,\n22:   preserving the existing ID/EX, EX/MEM, MEM/WB, forwarding, RVFI order, and\n23:   nret=1 retirement behavior.\n24: \n25:   This retiming should shorten the critical path from instruction memory into\n26:   decode/regfile/ID-EX control, improving Fmax without adding predictor muxes or\n27:   branch-immediate decode to the fetch next-PC path. The CPI cost should be\n28:   limited to pipeline fill and the existing redirect flush semantics; CoreMark's\n29:   bracketed region is long enough that a modest Fmax gain should dominate.\n30: expected_impact:\n31:   fitness_delta_pct: 4\n32:   confidence: medium\n33: changes:\n34:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n35:     description: \"Add a real IF/ID register for pc, instr, and valid; hold it on pipeline stalls and flush it on redirects or failed instruction fetches.\"\n36:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n37:     description: \"Adjust stall and flush semantics so the registered IF/ID boundary is held, bubbled, or cleared coherently under load-use, bus stalls, MDU busy, and redirects.\"\n38:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n39:     description: \"Wire the registered IF/ID control through the existing pipeline without changing the nret=1 RVFI port set or retirement boundary.\"\n40:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n41:     description: \"Keep ID decode behavior unchanged while consuming the newly registered IF/ID payload rather than a combinational fetch bundle.\"\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\ntitle: \"Register the IF ID boundary\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The current front end has no real IF/ID pipeline register: imem_data, PC,\n  decode, immediate generation, register-file address selection, and the ID/EX\n  capture all sit in one cycle. After the successful MDU split and metadata\n  pruning, the remaining Tang Nano 20K fitness is likely limited by routing and\n  long stage boundaries rather than by CoreMark CPI alone.\n\n  Prior structural and predictor attempts that added front-end speculation or\n  replay state regressed because they put new work on the fetch next-PC path.\n  A plain IF/ID register is a narrower structural retiming that does not try to\n  predict control flow; it simply cuts the fetch-to-decode path and lets the PC\n  and instruction memory interface settle before decode consumes the word.\nhypothesis: |\n  Convert the current combinational IF/ID bundle into a registered pipeline\n  boundary owned by if_stage. The IF stage should capture pc, instr, and valid\n  when imemReady is high and decode can advance; hold the registered bundle\n  during load-use, dmem, and MDU stalls; and flush it on redirects or invalid","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778663291120,"end":1778663291123}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01a343f169a454e4016a043f792ce0819a97ce42955121448b"}},"id":"prt_e2097f1be001qpjFS0J65NXUQt","sessionID":"ses_1df6a0176ffevdE76ufkR1w8iY","messageID":"msg_e2097c211001IuUlQie8CXZhf9"}}
