{"type":"text","timestamp":1778664193470,"sessionID":"ses_1df5b277effeiZDCj1aKs4bhnS","part":{"id":"prt_e20a5b1eb001DZ7qgvgMWmUdCu","messageID":"msg_e20a5269d001YyjwBwJGDc8FD8","sessionID":"ses_1df5b277effeiZDCj1aKs4bhnS","type":"text","text":"The prior structural wins and losses point away from fetch speculation/replay and toward retiming or decoupling that leaves IF next-PC untouched. I’m going to write a structural hypothesis that targets store backpressure with a tiny posted store buffer, while preserving in-order retirement and stalling later memory ops behind the buffer.","time":{"start":1778664190443,"end":1778664193469},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_023ea1de9b59c69b016a0442fe5758819abc92eb91dcd0e82a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
