iption: \"Replace the one-entry posted store buffer with a two-entry FIFO, drain oldest-first to dmem, enqueue stalled stores when space is available, and keep RVFI store retirement data tied to the current MEM instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Interpret the store-buffer-full signal as FIFO-full and continue stalling younger memory operations while any buffered store is pending, without stalling younger non-memory instructions.\"\n","additions":19,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778666687690,"end":1778666687692}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e97b1a2b58cfddc016a044cb58844819b835b146f783be350"}},"id":"prt_e20cba59c001Y85A7xjnC2qHnE","sessionID":"ses_1df34bcc7ffeyhdId4u5zcI80E","messageID":"msg_e20cb94e9001DZTmRFckVxG9vO"}}
