{"type":"text","timestamp":1778669597857,"sessionID":"ses_1df08510bffexrpR2l5Sr0w2ZL","part":{"id":"prt_e20f832cf001gi2yIwjSzNys5H","messageID":"msg_e20f7d9df001z0aPWYYfYGRXRA","sessionID":"ses_1df08510bffexrpR2l5Sr0w2ZL","type":"text","text":"Structural history confirms front-end retiming/prediction and deeper buffers have been costly, while reducing common-stage routing has paid off. I’m writing a focused hypothesis to precompute forwarding decisions in ID so EX no longer owns the source-register comparator cone.","time":{"start":1778669597391,"end":1778669597856},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_05e6604719c16156016a04581d44e0819991941b91cac4c033","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778669622456,"sessionID":"ses_1df08510bffexrpR2l5Sr0w2ZL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_cqElwz34c0bG3cypmjaECTSS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Precompute forwarding selects in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage resolves both operand-forwarding mux selects with two\n+  5-bit destination comparisons against EX/MEM and MEM/WB immediately before\n+  the ALU, branch comparator, MDU launch, and EX/MEM register boundary. After\n+  the successful MDU split, Tang Nano 20K fitness appears dominated by hot\n+  RV32I timing and routing rather than rare long-latency M operations.\n+\n+  Prior structural wins came from removing common-path pressure, while attempts\n+  to add front-end prediction, replay, or deeper queues regressed. Moving the\n+  forwarding compare work one stage earlier is a structural retiming that keeps\n+  fetch, branch resolution, memory ordering, and the nret=1 RVFI contract\n+  unchanged.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Compute the EX operand forwarding selects while the consumer instruction is\n+  still in ID, comparing IF/ID rs1/rs2 against the instruction currently in EX\n+  and the instruction currently in MEM. Latch those two 2-bit selects into the\n+  ID/EX payload, then make ex_stage use the precomputed selects directly for\n+  its rs1/rs2 muxes.\n+\n+  This removes forward_unit's register-number comparator cone from the EX-stage\n+  ALU/branch critical path and replaces it with four small control bits in the\n+  ID/EX register. The existing load-use stall remains authoritative, so a load\n+  immediately ahead of a consumer still bubbles rather than forwarding the\n+  address-valued EX/MEM result. RVFI source reporting remains based on the\n+  post-forward operands carried through EX/MEM/MEM/WB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add two 2-bit forwarding-select fields to id_ex_t so the decision can be carried into EX with the instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept producer rd/reg_write metadata for the instructions currently ahead in EX and MEM, compute rs1/rs2 forwarding selects during decode, and latch them into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the precomputed forwarding selects from id_ex_t instead of top-level forward_unit outputs for the operand muxes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the producer metadata into id_stage and remove the separate forward_unit instance from the EX critical path.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Precompute forwarding selects in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage resolves both operand-forwarding mux selects with two\n+  5-bit destination comparisons against EX/MEM and MEM/WB immediately before\n+  the ALU, branch comparator, MDU launch, and EX/MEM register boundary. After\n+  the successful MDU split, Tang Nano 20K fitness appears dominated by hot\n+  RV32I timing and routing rather than rare long-latency M operations.\n+\n+  Prior structural wins came from removing common-path pressure, while attempts\n+  to add front-end prediction, replay, or deeper queues regressed. Moving the\n+  forwarding compare work one stage earlier is a structural retiming that keeps\n+  fetch, branch resolution, memory ordering, and the nret=1 RVFI contract\n+  unchanged.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Compute the EX operand forwarding selects while the consumer instruction is\n+  still in ID, comparing IF/ID rs1/rs2 against the instruction currently in EX\n+  and the instruction currently in MEM. Latch those two 2-bit selects into the\n+  ID/EX payload, then make ex_stage use the precomputed selects directly for\n+  its rs1/rs2 muxes.\n+\n+  This removes forward_unit's register-number comparator cone from the EX-stage\n+  ALU/branch critical path and replaces it with four small control bits in the\n+  ID/EX register. The existing load-use stall remains authoritative, so a load\n+  immediately ahead of a consumer still bubbles rather than forwarding the\n+  address-valued EX/MEM result. RVFI source reporting remains based on the\n+  post-forward operands carried through EX/MEM/MEM/WB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add two 2-bit forwarding-select fields to id_ex_t so the decision can be carried into EX with the instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept producer rd/reg_write metadata for the instructions currently ahead in EX and MEM, compute rs1/rs2 forwarding selects during decode, and latch them into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the precomputed forwarding selects from id_ex_t instead of top-level forward_unit outputs for the operand muxes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the producer metadata into id_stage and remove the separate forward_unit instance from the EX critical path.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Precompute forwarding selects in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage resolves both operand-forwarding mux selects with two\n+  5-bit destination comparisons against EX/MEM and MEM/WB immediately before\n+  the ALU, branch comparator, MDU launch, and EX/MEM register boundary. After\n+  the successful MDU split, Tang Nano 20K fitness appears dominated by hot\n+  RV32I timing and routing rather than rare long-latency M operations.\n+\n+  Prior structural wins came from removing common-path pressure, while attempts\n+  to add front-end prediction, replay, or deeper queues regressed. Moving the\n+  forwarding compare work one stage earlier is a structural retiming that keeps\n+  fetch, branch resolution, memory ordering, and the nret=1 RVFI contract\n+  unchanged.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Compute the EX operand forwarding selects while the consumer instruction is\n+  still in ID, comparing IF/ID rs1/rs2 against the instruction currently in EX\n+  and the instruction currently in MEM. Latch those two 2-bit selects into the\n+  ID/EX payload, then make ex_stage use the precomputed selects directly for\n+  its rs1/rs2 muxes.\n+\n+  This removes forward_unit's register-number comparator cone from the EX-stage\n+  ALU/branch critical path and replaces it with four small control bits in the\n+  ID/EX register. The existing load-use stall remains authoritative, so a load\n+  immediately ahead of a consumer still bubbles rather than forwarding the\n+  address-valued EX/MEM result. RVFI source reporting remains based on the\n+  post-forward operands carried through EX/MEM/MEM/WB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add two 2-bit forwarding-select fields to id_ex_t so the decision can be carried into EX with the instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept producer rd/reg_write metadata for the instructions currently ahead in EX and MEM, compute rs1/rs2 forwarding selects during decode, and latch them into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the precomputed forwarding selects from id_ex_t instead of top-level forward_unit outputs for the operand muxes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the producer metadata into id_stage and remove the separate forward_unit instance from the EX critical path.\"\n","additions":40,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778669622451,"end":1778669622455}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05e6604719c16156016a04581dc4b481999bd35ff4683da192"}},"id":"prt_e20f834a1001J4f4JOY3bUttcj","sessionID":"ses_1df08510bffexrpR2l5Sr0w2ZL","messageID":"msg_e20f7d9df001z0aPWYYfYGRXRA"}}
