{"type":"text","timestamp":1778670672869,"sessionID":"ses_1def7f214ffeyFirOaJREhnwg4","part":{"id":"prt_e21089b13001I7Rk4jNj3Pv6aq","messageID":"msg_e21083921001QicBChe9fvqX9S","sessionID":"ses_1def7f214ffeyFirOaJREhnwg4","type":"text","text":"The log confirms front-end structural changes and deeper queues have mostly regressed, while narrow common-path pruning and the one-entry store buffer were the successful structural directions. I’m going to write a back-end/dataflow simplification hypothesis that avoids fetch and prediction logic.","time":{"start":1778670672659,"end":1778670672867},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a12eeaa498e523f016a045c508b88819a8f77e0087080a34d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778670695624,"sessionID":"ses_1def7f214ffeyFirOaJREhnwg4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_z8uc9Mxxbs3Ew2BlGqTBwUIM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: \"Register final writeback data\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM/WB boundary carries both alu_result and read_data plus a\n+  mem_to_reg control bit, then wb_stage selects the final value on the same\n+  path that drives regfile write data, MEM/WB forwarding, and RVFI rd_wdata.\n+  Prior successful structural work came from removing common-path pressure and\n+  pipeline metadata, while front-end replay/prediction changes and deeper\n+  queues have repeatedly regressed on Tang Nano 20K.\n+\n+  A narrow back-end retiming can reduce late writeback muxing and MEM/WB\n+  routing without touching fetch, branch resolution, memory ordering, the\n+  posted store buffer depth, or the nret=1 RVFI contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a final wb_data field to the MEM/WB payload and compute it inside\n+  mem_stage before the MEM/WB register captures: load instructions write the\n+  already sign/zero-extended load_data, while all other register-writing\n+  instructions write the EX/MEM alu_result. Then make wb_stage and the RVFI\n+  rd_wdata path consume the registered wb_data directly, and remove the\n+  late mem_to_reg read_data/alu_result mux from the writeback/forwarding path.\n+\n+  Unlike the earlier mem_to_reg pruning attempt, this does not make mem_read\n+  drive a wider fanout cone. It preserves the existing load extraction logic\n+  and simply registers the selected result at the stage boundary, reducing\n+  MEM/WB payload width and simplifying the high-fanout WB data source used by\n+  the regfile and EX forwarding.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Replace MEM/WB read_data/alu_result result payload with a registered final wb_data field while keeping RVFI memory sideband fields intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute final writeback data before the MEM/WB register captures, using load_data for loads and the ALU result otherwise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive the regfile write port directly from the registered MEM/WB wb_data field instead of a late mem_to_reg mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Use the registered wb_data value for RVFI rd_wdata and MEM/WB forwarding while preserving single-channel retirement order.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: \"Register final writeback data\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM/WB boundary carries both alu_result and read_data plus a\n+  mem_to_reg control bit, then wb_stage selects the final value on the same\n+  path that drives regfile write data, MEM/WB forwarding, and RVFI rd_wdata.\n+  Prior successful structural work came from removing common-path pressure and\n+  pipeline metadata, while front-end replay/prediction changes and deeper\n+  queues have repeatedly regressed on Tang Nano 20K.\n+\n+  A narrow back-end retiming can reduce late writeback muxing and MEM/WB\n+  routing without touching fetch, branch resolution, memory ordering, the\n+  posted store buffer depth, or the nret=1 RVFI contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a final wb_data field to the MEM/WB payload and compute it inside\n+  mem_stage before the MEM/WB register captures: load instructions write the\n+  already sign/zero-extended load_data, while all other register-writing\n+  instructions write the EX/MEM alu_result. Then make wb_stage and the RVFI\n+  rd_wdata path consume the registered wb_data directly, and remove the\n+  late mem_to_reg read_data/alu_result mux from the writeback/forwarding path.\n+\n+  Unlike the earlier mem_to_reg pruning attempt, this does not make mem_read\n+  drive a wider fanout cone. It preserves the existing load extraction logic\n+  and simply registers the selected result at the stage boundary, reducing\n+  MEM/WB payload width and simplifying the high-fanout WB data source used by\n+  the regfile and EX forwarding.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Replace MEM/WB read_data/alu_result result payload with a registered final wb_data field while keeping RVFI memory sideband fields intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute final writeback data before the MEM/WB register captures, using load_data for loads and the ALU result otherwise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive the regfile write port directly from the registered MEM/WB wb_data field instead of a late mem_to_reg mux.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Use the registered wb_data value for RVFI rd_wdata and MEM/WB forwarding while preserving single-channel retirement order.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-00