{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778671915347,"sessionID":"ses_1dee5ad85ffeMCgdyu2m0J6hqP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_LRaKHd4ZpH0C9z948nmPb7Lr","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Metadata-free loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still pays a two-instruction EX redirect penalty on taken\n+  CoreMark loop backedges, but prior predictor attempts regressed mostly by\n+  adding IF immediate decode, broad prediction metadata, extra redirect sources,\n+  or learned tables that widened the fragile fetch and EX control paths. The\n+  remaining predictor opportunity is therefore not a stronger predictor, but a\n+  narrower one: keep only the single hot-loop target case and remove the carried\n+  predicted-next-PC metadata that hurt earlier variants.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry taken-backedge predictor that records only the PC and target\n+  of the most recent valid taken conditional branch whose target is below its PC.\n+  IF predicts by exact PC match and selects the registered target; otherwise it\n+  keeps the existing pc+4 path. Unlike the prior single-entry and next-line\n+  attempts, do not add predicted target fields to IF/ID or ID/EX. EX can infer\n+  whether this instruction was predicted from the same stable predictor entry\n+  using its retiring branch PC, suppress the duplicate redirect only when the\n+  actual taken target matches the entry, and redirect to pc+4 on a predicted-hit\n+  loop exit.\n+\n+  This preserves EX as the authoritative resolver and keeps RVFI pc_wdata/order\n+  semantics unchanged while reducing prediction metadata routing. The expected\n+  gain is small, but this is the predictor variant most directly aimed at the\n+  known failure mode: target prediction cost, not predictor accuracy.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one registered backedge PC/target entry, predict only on exact PC match, and keep all non-hit fetches on the existing pc+4 path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the single-entry predictor from resolved taken backward conditional branches, infer predicted hits from the stable entry, suppress duplicate redirects on matching targets, and repair loop exits to pc+4.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the minimal predictor update and predicted-hit information between IF and EX without changing the nret=1 RVFI port set.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Metadata-free loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still pays a two-instruction EX redirect penalty on taken\n+  CoreMark loop backedges, but prior predictor attempts regressed mostly by\n+  adding IF immediate decode, broad prediction metadata, extra redirect sources,\n+  or learned tables that widened the fragile fetch and EX control paths. The\n+  remaining predictor opportunity is therefore not a stronger predictor, but a\n+  narrower one: keep only the single hot-loop target case and remove the carried\n+  predicted-next-PC metadata that hurt earlier v