{"type":"text","timestamp":1778672609580,"sessionID":"ses_1deda8372ffeUWTMBfUgq7gdaD","part":{"id":"prt_e21262179001v9VL0bp259AVhU","messageID":"msg_e21261a93001l6q74yQkQfM4o4","sessionID":"ses_1deda8372ffeUWTMBfUgq7gdaD","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a low-confidence predictor hypothesis that narrows the prior loop predictor: stable per-instruction prediction metadata, no IF decode, no multi-entry tables, and only a one-entry learned backedge.","time":{"start":1778672607609,"end":1778672609580},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ab69dd759e88e2d016a0463df744c819bb562a536367dad10","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778672633284,"sessionID":"ses_1deda8372ffeUWTMBfUgq7gdaD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_2JWFFc3jsrdvNJhQyzRDIIAA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Stable one-entry loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still pays a two-instruction EX redirect penalty for every\n+  taken loop backedge, but the predictor history shows that broad IF decode,\n+  target tables, return stacks, and wide predicted-next-PC metadata consistently\n+  lose Fmax or break RVFI pc_fwd semantics. The one useful predictor target is\n+  still CoreMark's recurring counted-loop backedges, provided the design keeps\n+  the fetch path and metadata smaller than prior attempts.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry learned backedge predictor with stable per-instruction\n+  prediction identity rather than mutable-state inference. EX records only a\n+  valid bit, branch PC, target, and a one-bit generation toggle when a valid\n+  conditional branch is taken to a lower PC. IF predicts only on exact PC match\n+  to that registered entry and selects the registered target instead of pc+4;\n+  there is no IF immediate decode, BHT, BTB array, RAS, or jump prediction.\n+\n+  Carry only `pred_backedge` and the entry generation bit through IF/ID and\n+  ID/EX. EX suppresses the duplicate redirect only when the resolved branch PC,\n+  target, and generation still match the prediction captured with that\n+  instruction; otherwise it uses the existing redirect/flush recovery. This\n+  fixes the prior metadata-free correctness hazard without carrying a full\n+  predicted target through the pipeline, aiming for a small CPI gain on hot\n+  loops with less routing cost than earlier predictor variants.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal prediction metadata fields, `pred_backedge` and a one-bit predictor generation, to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single-entry registered backedge predictor lookup on exact PC match, update hooks from EX, and emit the small prediction metadata with fetched instructions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the backedge predictor from resolved taken conditional branches and validate captured prediction metadata before suppressing or repairing redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and validation signals between IF and EX while preserving the nret=1 RVFI interface and existing bus stall behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Stable one-entry loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core still pays a two-instruction EX redirect penalty for every\n+  taken loop backedge, but the predictor history shows that broad IF decode,\n+  target tables, return stacks, and wide predicted-next-PC metadata consistently\n+  lose Fmax or break RVFI pc_fwd semantics. The one useful predictor target is\n+  still CoreMark's recurring counted-loop backedges, provided the design keeps\n+  the fetch path and metadata smaller than prior attempts.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry learned backedge predictor with stable per-instruction\n+  prediction identity rather than mutable-state inference. EX records only a\n+  valid bit, branch PC, target, and a one-bit generation toggle when a valid\n+  conditional branch is taken to a lower PC. IF predicts only on exact PC match\n+  to that registered entry and selects the registered target instead of pc+4;\n+  there is no IF immediate decode, BHT, BTB array, RAS, or jump prediction.\n+\n+  Carry only `pred_backedge` and the entry generation bit through IF/ID and\n+  ID/EX. EX suppresses the duplicate redirect only when the resolved branch PC,\n+  target, and generation still match the prediction captured with that\n+  instruction; otherwise it uses the existing redirect/flush recovery. This\n+  fixes the prior metadata-free correctness hazard without carrying a full\n+  predicted target through the pipeline, aiming for a small CPI gain on hot\n+  loops with less routing cost than earlier predictor variants.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal prediction metadata fields, `pred_backedge` and a one-bit predictor generation, to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single-entry registered backedge predictor lookup on exact PC match, update hooks from EX, and emit the small prediction metadata with fetched instructions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the backedge predictor from resolved taken conditional branches and validate captured prediction metadata before suppressing or repairing redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and validation signals between IF and EX while preserving the nret=1 RVFI interface and existing bus stall b