{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778673538526,"sessionID":"ses_1decbe4fcffenDghaxHGY347YM","part":{"id":"prt_e213455dc001wCZJFDj3YcEAFB","messageID":"msg_e21344ff8001Je6izJXLARpMnk","sessionID":"ses_1decbe4fcffenDghaxHGY347YM","snapshot":"42653fa39905d06362a6fd015602721f9365bb1e","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778673561480,"sessionID":"ses_1decbe4fcffenDghaxHGY347YM","part":{"id":"prt_e2134adc4001s5e075OQUJzO3o","messageID":"msg_e21344ff8001Je6izJXLARpMnk","sessionID":"ses_1decbe4fcffenDghaxHGY347YM","type":"text","text":"The predictor history is consistently negative when speculation touches the no-stall IF next-PC mux or carries wide prediction metadata. I’m going to write a narrower hypothesis that only predicts during already-stalled front-end cycles, so it targets CPI recovery without lengthening the normal fetch path.","time":{"start":1778673561028,"end":1778673561479},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0afa86f67cc342c7016a046798e6a8819a97f91cc86db29ba4","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778673585885,"sessionID":"ses_1decbe4fcffenDghaxHGY347YM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ip3qS9UQu4PjZYiVT5GYtKdw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Stall-shadow branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core consistently lost fitness when they put\n+  target lookup, immediate decode, extra PC muxing, or broad prediction metadata\n+  on the normal no-stall fetch path. CoreMark still pays taken-control penalties,\n+  but the benchmark also injects random instruction and data stalls that leave\n+  the front end holding a fetched instruction for one or more cycles. Those held\n+  cycles are an opportunity to prepare a redirect without lengthening the common\n+  pc+4 fetch path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a stall-shadow predictor that only becomes active while IF/ID is already\n+  blocked by imem backpressure, dmem backpressure, load-use, or MDU busy. During\n+  those held cycles, decode the currently presented instruction enough to\n+  identify direct JAL and backward conditional-branch candidates and compute\n+  their static target off the normal PC-update critical path. When the stall\n+  releases, IF may use this precomputed target for a one-cycle early redirect;\n+  EX remains authoritative and uses a single carried predicted-shadow bit plus\n+  predicted target to suppress the duplicate redirect only on an exact match or\n+  repair through the existing redirect/flush path on mismatch.\n+\n+  This deliberately avoids BTB/BHT arrays, return stacks, same-cycle IF decode,\n+  and prediction on uninterrupted fetch cycles. It should recover some control\n+  penalty after random stall windows in CoreMark while leaving the proven normal\n+  fetch path, memory ordering, RVFI order, and nret=1 top-level interface intact.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal shadow-prediction metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX: a valid bit and predicted target for instructions redirected from a stalled fetch window.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and latch direct JAL/backward-branch shadow targets only while the front end is already stalled, then use the latched target when the stall releases.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the shadow-predicted target against the authoritative resolved next PC, suppress duplicate redirects only on exact matches, and otherwise use the existing redirect recovery.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the shadow-prediction metadata between IF and EX without changing the nret=1 RVFI port set or memory interfaces.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,38 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Stall-shadow branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core consistently lost fitness when they put\n+  target lookup, immediate decode, extra PC muxing, or broad prediction metadata\n+  on the normal no-stall fetch path. CoreMark still pays taken-control penalties,\n+  but the benchmark also injects random instruction and data stalls that leave\n+  the front end holding a fetched instruction for one or more cycles. Those held\n+  cycles are an opportunity to prepare a redirect without lengthening the common\n+  pc+4 fetch path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a stall-shadow predictor that only becomes active while IF/ID is already\n+  blocked by imem backpressure, dmem backpressure, load-use, or MDU busy. During\n+  those held cycles, decode the currently presented instruction enough to\n+  identify direct JAL and backward conditional-branch candidates and compute\n+  their static target off the normal PC-update critical path. When the stall\n+  releases, IF may use this precomputed target for a one-cycle early redirect;\n+  EX remains authoritative and uses a single carried predicted-shadow bit plus\n+  predicted target to suppress the duplicate redirect only on an exact match or\n+  repair through the existing redirect/flush path on mismatch.\n+\n+  This deliberately avoids BTB/BHT arrays, return stacks, same-cycle IF decode,\n+  and prediction on uninterrupted fetch cycles. It should recover some control\n+  penalty after random stall windows in CoreMark while leaving the proven normal\n+  fetch path, memory ordering, RVFI order, and nret=1 top-level interface intact.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal shadow-prediction metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX: a valid bit and predicted target for instructions redirected from a stalled fetch window.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and latch direct JAL/backward-branch shadow targets only while the front end is already stalled, then use the latched target when the stall releases.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the shadow-predicted target against the authoritative resolved next PC, suppress duplicate redirects only on exact matches, and otherwise use the existing redirect recovery.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the shadow-prediction metadata between IF and EX without changing the nret=1 RVFI port set or memory interfaces.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,38 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Stall-shadow branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core consistently lost fitness when they put\n+  target lookup, immediate decode, extra PC muxing, or broad prediction metadata\n+  on the normal no-stall fetch path. CoreMark still pays taken-control penalties,\n+  but the benchmark also injects random instruction and data stalls that leave\n+  the front end holding a fetched instruction for one or more cycles. Those held\n+  cycles are an opportunity to prepare a redirect without lengthening the common\n+  pc+4 fetch path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a stall-shadow predictor that only becomes active while IF/ID is already\n+  blocked by imem backpressure, dmem backpressure, load-use, or MDU busy. During\n+  those held cycles, decode the currently presented instruction enough to\n+  identify direct JAL and backward conditional-branch candidates and compute\n+  their static target off the normal PC-update critical path. When the stall\n+  releases, IF may use this precomputed target for a one-cycle early redirect;\n+  EX remains authoritative and uses a single carried predicted-shadow bit plus\n+  predicted target to suppress the duplicate redirect only on an exact match or\n+  repair through the existing redirect/flush path on mismatch.\n+\n+  This deliberately avoids BTB/BHT arrays, return stacks, same-cycle IF decode,\n+  and prediction on uninterrupted fetch cycles. It should recover some control\n+  penalty after random stall windows in CoreMark while leaving the proven normal\n+  fetch path, memory ordering, RVFI order, and nret=1 top-level interface intact.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal shadow-prediction metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX: a valid bit and predicted target for instructions redirected from a stalled fetch window.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and latch direct JAL/backward-branch shadow targets only while the front end is already stalled, then use the latched target when the stall releases.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the shadow-predicted target against the authoritative resolved next PC, suppress duplicate redirects only on exact matches, and otherwise use the existing redirect recovery.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the shadow-prediction metadata between IF and EX without changing the nret=1 RVFI port set or memory interfaces.\"\n","additions":38,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778673585881,"end":1778673585884}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0afa86f67cc342c7016a04679954e0819aacadbacdda84c3fd"}},"id":"prt_e2134af89001plf6XseDsuMgvg","sessionID":"ses_1decbe4fcf