{"type":"text","timestamp":1778674531131,"sessionID":"ses_1debd2588ffexHopAr9k3ykg5X","part":{"id":"prt_e2143757c001hpMYoq0yPXnBUM","messageID":"msg_e2143198b001Mf7RWxv0uMJvPs","sessionID":"ses_1debd2588ffexHopAr9k3ykg5X","type":"text","text":"The log confirms the main constraint for this slot: prior predictors lost by adding work to the normal IF next-PC path or broad prediction metadata. I’m writing a deliberately narrow predictor hypothesis that only trains on unconditional JAL call sites and uses stable per-instruction metadata, with low expected impact because the category has been consistently timing-sensitive.","time":{"start":1778674529660,"end":1778674531130},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_001ac77e85be8470016a046b618ce0819abc5e897abc86dafc","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778674558207,"sessionID":"ses_1debd2588ffexHopAr9k3ykg5X","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_H1wX0fl1WeK3qJLsyrcEQ8A5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Tiny learned JAL predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The predictor history for this core shows that branch-direction tables, loop\n+  target caches, return stacks, and static immediate decoding usually lose more\n+  Tang Nano 20K Fmax than they recover in CoreMark CPI. The remaining useful\n+  predictor target should therefore avoid conditional branches, JALR returns,\n+  IF immediate decoding, and wide predicted-next-PC metadata.\n+\n+  Direct JAL call and jump sites are always taken and have stable targets in\n+  CoreMark. Learning only the most recent direct JAL target gives a predictor\n+  that can recover recurring call/jump flushes with a single PC compare and a\n+  registered target, rather than a general branch predictor.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry learned direct-JAL target predictor. When EX resolves a valid\n+  JAL, record the JAL PC, resolved target, and a one-bit generation tag. IF\n+  predicts only when the current PC exactly matches that registered JAL PC,\n+  selecting the registered target instead of pc+4; all conditional branches,\n+  JALR, forward/backward branch heuristics, and return prediction remain on the\n+  existing non-speculative path.\n+\n+  Carry only a predicted_jal bit and generation tag through IF/ID and ID/EX.\n+  EX remains authoritative: it suppresses the duplicate redirect only when the\n+  resolved instruction is a JAL whose PC and generation match the prediction,\n+  otherwise it uses the existing redirect/flush repair path. This should be\n+  cheaper than prior predictors because the target is learned from EX rather\n+  than decoded in IF, and the metadata is narrower than a full predicted target.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add narrow predicted-JAL metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry learned JAL PC/target predictor, select the registered target on exact PC hit, and expose prediction metadata with the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train the JAL predictor from resolved JALs and suppress duplicate redirects only when the captured prediction identity matches the resolving instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor train signals and predicted-JAL metadata between IF and EX while preserving existing hazard, flush, and RVFI retirement behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Tiny learned JAL predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The predictor history for this core shows that branch-direction tables, loop\n+  target caches, return stacks, and static immediate decoding usually lose more\n+  Tang Nano 20K Fmax than they recover in CoreMark CPI. The remaining useful\n+  predictor target should therefore avoid conditional branches, JALR returns,\n+  IF immediate decoding, and wide predicted-next-PC metadata.\n+\n+  Direct JAL call and jump sites are always taken and have stable targets in\n+  CoreMark. Learning only the most recent direct JAL target gives a predictor\n+  that can recover recurring call/jump flushes with a single PC compare and a\n+  registered target, rather than a general branch predictor.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry learned direct-JAL target predictor. When EX resolves a valid\n+  JAL, record the JAL PC, resolved target, and a one-bit generation tag. IF\n+  predicts only when the current PC exactly matches that registered JAL PC,\n+  selecting the registered target instead of pc+4; all conditional branches,\n+  JALR, forward/backward branch heuristics, and return prediction remain on the\n+  existing non-speculative path.\n+\n+  Carry only a predicted_jal bit and generation tag through IF/ID and ID/EX.\n+  EX remains authoritative: it suppresses the duplicate redirect only when the\n+  resolved instruction is a JAL whose PC and generation match the prediction,\n+  otherwise it uses the existing redirect/flush repair path. This should be\n+  cheaper than prior predictors because the target is learned from EX rather\n+  than decoded in IF, and the metadata is narrower than a full predicted target.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add narrow predicted-JAL metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry learned JAL PC/target predictor, select the registered target on exact PC hit, and expose prediction metadata with the fetched instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train the JAL predictor from resolved JALs and suppress duplicate redirects only when the captured prediction i