hot EX stage.\n23: expected_impact:\n24:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n25:   confidence: medium\n26: changes:\n27:   - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n28:     description: \"Change the forwarding unit outputs from two 2-bit select buses to direct EX/MEM and MEM/WB hit signals per source operand, preserving EX/MEM priority and local rd!=0 checks.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Consume direct forwarding hit controls in the rs1/rs2 muxes instead of decoding 2-bit select values, with identical operand priority and fallback behavior.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n32:     description: \"Update the top-level forwarding wires and module connections to carry the direct hit controls between forward_unit and ex_stage.\"\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r15s0\ntitle: Direct forwarding hit controls\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current best bench core is timing-sensitive, and the only recent wins\n  came from reducing hot-path routing without changing pipeline behavior.\n  The EX operand path still builds two 2-bit forwarding select values in\n  forward_unit, routes them into ex_stage, and decodes them back into mux\n  choices for rs1 and rs2. That small encoder/decode layer sits directly on\n  the forwarding-to-ALU/branch compare path that CoreMark exercises heavily.\nhypothesis: |\n  Replace the 2-bit forwarding select interface with direct one-hot producer\n  hit controls for each operand, for example fwd_rs1_exmem, fwd_rs1_memwb,\n  fwd_rs2_exmem, and fwd_rs2_memwb. Keep the existing priority of EX/MEM over\n  MEM/WB inside the EX operand mux, and preserve the current rd!=0 checks and\n  producer sidebands so this does not repeat the failed x0 pre-gating attempt.\n\n  This is a pure micro-optimization: it does not change CPI, load-use stalls,\n  memory ordering, MDU behavior, RVFI reporting, or the nret=1 IO contract.\n  The expected benefit is a modest median Fmax improvement by removing the","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778676451123,"end":1778676451131}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01c47f6c50f972ed016a0472e246588198a18b12dae0da3e85"}},"id":"prt_e2160c452001DJ5zYrLqkloyaC","sessionID":"ses_1dea0529effeId8FfAqyrGvnGe","messageID":"msg_e2160af6d001JJDwGEeCW0WQLG"}}
