{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778676475886,"sessionID":"ses_1dea0529effeId8FfAqyrGvnGe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_BQHywP7mAmrWv6A6zAUsT5Kx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\n+title: Registered next-PC hint predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core repeatedly lost fitness because they\n+  added same-cycle IF decode, table reads, target muxing, return-stack logic,\n+  or wide predicted-next-PC metadata to timing-sensitive fetch and execute\n+  paths. The remaining control-flow opportunity is to reduce taken-loop flushes\n+  only when the predictor decision can be prepared one cycle early and consumed\n+  as a tiny registered hint, rather than as a fresh lookup in the PC update cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry registered next-PC hint predictor for learned taken\n+  conditional backedges. When EX resolves a valid taken branch whose target is\n+  below its PC, record the branch PC, target, and a one-bit generation tag. While\n+  IF is fetching the previous sequential PC, compare pc+4 against the recorded\n+  branch PC and register a hint for the following cycle; if the next PC reaches\n+  that hinted branch, the PC update mux consumes only the registered hint target.\n+\n+  Carry only a predicted_hint bit and generation tag with the instruction so EX\n+  can suppress the duplicate redirect only when the resolved branch still\n+  matches the captured entry; otherwise the existing redirect/flush path repairs\n+  execution. This intentionally avoids BTB/BHT arrays, IF immediate decode,\n+  JAL/JALR prediction, and full predicted-target metadata, aiming for a small\n+  CPI gain on CoreMark loops with less Fmax risk than prior predictor variants.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-hint and generation metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles, avoiding full predicted target fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement the one-entry backedge record, prior-cycle pc+4 hint preparation, and registered hint target selection in the PC update path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Validate hinted branches against the captured generation and resolved target, suppressing duplicate redirects only on exact matches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and validation signals between IF and EX without changing the nret=1 top-level RVFI interface.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\n+title: Registered next-PC hint predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core repeatedly lost fitness because they\n+  added same-cycle IF decode, table reads, target muxing, return-stack logic,\n+  or wide predicted-next-PC metadata to timing-sensitive fetch and execute\n+  paths. The remaining control-flow opportunity is to reduce taken-loop flushes\n+  only when the predictor decision can be prepared one cycle early and consumed\n+  as a tiny registered hint, rather than as a fresh lookup in the PC update cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry