{"type":"text","timestamp":1778657255429,"sessionID":"ses_1dfc49ea4ffeSK9JEwsQSAHpsJ","part":{"id":"prt_e203bdc9c001CV0M8r59K4NWhb","messageID":"msg_e203bb1e5001lpQ4U3JCT5pw03","sessionID":"ses_1dfc49ea4ffeSK9JEwsQSAHpsJ","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a single predictor-focused hypothesis: a tiny direct-mapped BTB plus 2-bit BHT in IF, verified in EX, to avoid the current fixed fall-through penalty on CoreMark’s loop branches without changing NRET or the external IO contract.","time":{"start":1778657254556,"end":1778657255427},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_072e9c81eb6efd21016a0427e67440819b8ca3eca0dc1d65eb","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778657268392,"sessionID":"ses_1dfc49ea4ffeSK9JEwsQSAHpsJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_qGIikPYV40Ly3OPIQS3QsQCd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Add tiny BTB and BHT branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline always fetches pc+4 and resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken control-flow instruction pays a two-instruction wrong-path flush. CoreMark contains tight loops and repeated call/return style control flow where even a very small FPGA-friendly predictor should learn the hot backedges and reduce bubbles. A predictor is especially attractive under the random instruction-stall workload because it improves useful fetch placement without adding memory-system complexity.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped branch target buffer with 2-bit saturating direction counters in the IF stage. The IF stage predicts taken when the PC tag hits and the BHT counter is weak/strong taken, uses the cached target as next_pc, and carries predicted_pc/predicted_taken metadata down the pipeline. EX compares the actual resolved next PC against the prediction, redirects only on mispredict, and updates the BTB/BHT for branches and jumps. This should preserve correctness through the existing redirect/flush machinery while converting most steady-state CoreMark loop backedges from taken-branch flushes into correctly predicted fetches.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles with predicted_taken and predicted_pc metadata used for EX-stage mispredict detection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a tiny direct-mapped BTB plus 2-bit BHT, use it to choose next_pc, and expose update inputs from EX for resolved branches and jumps.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare predicted next PC with the resolved branch/jump/fall-through PC, assert redirect only on mispredict, and emit predictor update information.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor metadata and update signals between IF and EX while preserving the existing single-retire RVFI and memory IO contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat EX mispredict redirects like the existing redirect flush path so wrong-path IF/ID and ID/EX instructions are killed without changing load-use or dmem-stall behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Add tiny BTB and BHT branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage pipeline always fetches pc+4 and resolves all branches and jumps in EX, so every taken control-flow instruction pays a two-instruction wrong-path flush. CoreMark contains tight loops and repeated call/return style control flow where even a very small FPGA-friendly predictor should learn the hot backedges and reduce bubbles. A predictor is especially attractive under the random instruction-stall workload because it improves useful fetch placement without adding memory-system complexity.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped branch target buffer with 2-bit saturating direction counters in the IF stage. The IF stage predicts taken when the PC tag hits and the BHT counter is weak/strong taken, uses the cached target as next_pc, and carries predicted_pc/predicted_taken metadata down the pipeline. EX compares the actual resolved next PC against the prediction, redirects only on mispredict, and updates the BTB/BHT for branches and jumps. This should preserve correctness through the existing redirect/flush machinery while converting most steady-state CoreMark loop backedges from taken-branch flushes into correctly predicted fetches.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles with predicted_taken and predicted_pc metadata used for EX-stage mispredict detection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a tiny direct-mapped BTB plus 2-bit BHT, use it to choose next_pc, and expose update inputs from EX for resolved branches and jumps.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare predicted next PC with the resolved branch/jump/fall-through PC, assert redirect only on mispredict, and emit predictor update information.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor metadata and update signals between IF and EX while preserving the existing single-retire RVFI and memory IO contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat EX mispredict redirects like the existing redirect flush path so wrong-path IF/ID and ID/EX instructions are killed without changing load-use or dmem-stall behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypot