{"type":"text","timestamp":1778659613304,"sessionID":"ses_1dfa17421ffe8xxzwNBheVVYJ3","part":{"id":"prt_e205fd99900184bTnLfuZ1y2A5","messageID":"msg_e205f6385002dGW3fSchTpk17a","sessionID":"ses_1dfa17421ffe8xxzwNBheVVYJ3","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor failed because it changed redirect behavior without carrying enough prediction metadata for RVFI/pc_fwd correctness. I’m writing a narrower static direct-control predictor hypothesis: predict only backward conditional branches and direct JAL targets in IF, carry predicted next-PC metadata, and let EX redirect only when predicted next-PC differs from actual.","time":{"start":1778659613081,"end":1778659613303},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_077a97ea4c8ce344016a04311cf8f08199abf1ee8cf019180c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778659638830,"sessionID":"ses_1dfa17421ffe8xxzwNBheVVYJ3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_F0UgCyPi0vpwQrJiSl4INCJA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\n+title: Static backward branch predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core always fetches pc+4 and pays a two-instruction\n+  redirect penalty for every taken branch and jump resolved in EX. CoreMark has\n+  many small counted loops where backward conditional branches are taken most\n+  iterations, plus direct JAL call/loop control transfers with targets fully\n+  encoded in the fetched instruction. A tiny static predictor can recover much\n+  of that CPI loss with less state and less correctness risk than the previous\n+  BTB/BHT attempt.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add decode-light prediction in IF for direct control flow only: predict JAL\n+  taken to its J-immediate target, predict conditional branches with negative\n+  B-immediates taken, and leave forward branches plus JALR as pc+4. Carry the\n+  predicted next PC with the instruction through IF/ID and ID/EX. EX still\n+  computes the authoritative next PC and RVFI pc_wdata, but redirects and\n+  flushes only when the predicted next PC differs from the actual next PC.\n+  This keeps the existing retirement semantics intact while eliminating the\n+  steady-state flush on hot backward CoreMark loop branches and direct jumps.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can compare speculation against the resolved next PC without changing RVFI retirement fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute a static BTFNT/direct-JAL predicted next PC from the fetched instruction and update the PC with that prediction when not stalled or redirected.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pipeline the IF-stage predicted next PC alongside the decoded instruction into ID/EX, preserving bubbles and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare actual resolved next PC against the predicted next PC, assert redirect only on mismatch, and continue reporting actual pc_next for RVFI.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\n+title: Static backward branch predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core always fetches pc+4 and pays a two-instruction\n+  redirect penalty for every taken branch and jump resolved in EX. CoreMark has\n+  many small counted loops where backward conditional branches are taken most\n+  iterations, plus direct JAL call/loop control transfers with targets fully\n+  encoded in the fetched instruction. A tiny static predictor can recover much\n+  of that CPI loss with less state and less correctness risk than the previous\n+  BTB/BHT attempt.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add decode-light prediction in IF for direct control flow only: predict JAL\n+  taken to its J-immediate target, predict conditional branches with negative\n+  B-immediates taken, and leave forward branches plus JALR as pc+4. Carry the\n+  predicted next PC with the instruction through IF/ID and ID/EX. EX still\n+  computes the authoritative next PC and RVFI pc_wdata, but redirects and\n+  flushes only when the predicted next PC differs from the actual next PC.\n+  This keeps the existing retirement semantics intact while eliminating the\n+  steady-state flush on hot backward CoreMark loop branches and direct jumps.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can compare speculation against the resolved next PC without changing RVFI retirement fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute a static BTFNT/direct-JAL predicted next PC from the fetched instruction and update the PC with that prediction when not stalled or redirected.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pipeline the IF-stage predicted next PC alongside the decoded instruction into ID/EX, preserving bubbles and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare actual resolved next PC against the predicted next PC, assert redirect only on mismatch, and continue reporting actual pc_next for RVFI.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/