{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778661469853,"sessionID":"ses_1df852f7bffeGBB4ttvGuOvBDD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_tE2o8qAsFv94xaY4YyOuHl08","state":{"status":"error","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Tiny return address predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The previous predictor attempts show that putting branch-immediate decode or\n+  BTB/BHT lookup directly on the IF next-PC path can either break RVFI redirect\n+  semantics or lose enough Fmax to erase loop CPI gains. CoreMark still has many\n+  call and return transfers, and returns are expensive in the current core\n+  because every JALR resolves in EX and flushes two younger instructions.\n+\n+  A very small return-address predictor targets only the indirect-control case\n+  that static backward prediction cannot cover, while avoiding a broad branch\n+  direction predictor in the fetch critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a 2- or 4-entry return-address stack that pushes pc+4 for ordinary direct\n+  calls and predicts JALR returns when the fetched instruction matches the\n+  standard return shape, such as JALR x0, x1, 0 or JALR x0, x5, 0. The IF stage\n+  should keep the normal pc+4 path for all other instructions, so the added\n+  logic is a narrow opcode/funct/rd/rs1/imm equality check plus a small mux to a\n+  registered stack top.\n+\n+  Carry predicted-next-PC metadata with the instruction and keep EX as the\n+  authoritative resolver. On mismatch, use the existing redirect/flush path; on\n+  match, suppress only the unnecessary redirect flush while preserving RVFI\n+  pc_wdata from EX/MEM. Update the stack from resolved JAL/JALR instructions so\n+  stalls and mispredict flushes do not corrupt speculative state. This should\n+  reduce CoreMark function-return bubbles with lower Fmax risk than full branch\n+  prediction or decode-heavy backward prediction.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX-stage mispredict comparison without changing RVFI retirement fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a tiny committed return-address stack, predict only recognized return-form JALR instructions to the registered stack top, and otherwise keep the existing pc+4 fetch path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare predicted next PC against the resolved branch/jump next PC, redirect only on mismatches, and emit call/return update information for the return stack.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire prediction metadata and return-stack update signals between IF and EX while preserving the nret=1 top-level port contract.\"\n+*** End Patch"},"error":"apply_patch verification failed: Error: Invalid patch format: missing Begin/End markers","time":{"start":1778661469851,"end":1778661469852}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e01c84f1d1705b4016a043839fc0c819883ccb8455ed6f5ba"}},"id":"prt_e207ba2fd001uOxgbRlzbdE0iX","sessionID":"ses_1df852f7bffeGBB4ttvGuOvBDD","messageID":"msg_e207b7d4b001OmxHWWW8S5819E"}}
