{"type":"text","timestamp":1778664180406,"sessionID":"ses_1df5b2859ffeln6y4cMtuSf6LS","part":{"id":"prt_e20a58584001B7AxYwxKtr1b2H","messageID":"msg_e20a51346001823LyQ3F20Hu9Q","sessionID":"ses_1df5b2859ffeln6y4cMtuSf6LS","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts consistently lost Fmax when prediction logic sat directly on the IF next-PC path. The new hypothesis will move the predictor decision to ID with a tiny learned target table, aiming to recover one redirect cycle on hot taken branches while keeping IF mostly unchanged.","time":{"start":1778664179076,"end":1778664180406},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_090e735e80e99ec6016a0442f2ee94819aa8349502fa1483f5","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778664217470,"sessionID":"ses_1df5b2859ffeln6y4cMtuSf6LS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_YYql3mwH2qJfLX6Htyhug0pb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r5s2\n+title: \"ID-stage learned target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because opcode/immediate decode,\n+  BTB comparisons, return-shape checks, and predicted-next-PC muxing were placed on\n+  the IF next-PC path. CoreMark still pays a two-instruction penalty on recurring\n+  taken loop branches and direct jumps, so the remaining promising predictor angle\n+  is to avoid the IF critical path while still reducing taken-control bubbles.\n+\n+  A predictor consulted in ID can use the already-fetched PC/instruction timing\n+  point and redirect one cycle earlier than the current EX resolver. It only saves\n+  one of the two wrong-path slots, but it should cost less Fmax than full IF\n+  speculation and does not require early operand compare or immediate generation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped learned target predictor that is read in ID rather than\n+  IF. EX remains the authoritative resolver and updates a small table with the PC,\n+  resolved target, and a 2-bit taken counter for valid branches and jumps. When an\n+  instruction reaches ID, the predictor checks the IF/ID PC against the table tag;\n+  on a taken hit it sends an early redirect to IF using the stored target and marks\n+  the ID/EX payload with the predicted next PC.\n+\n+  EX still computes the actual next PC and RVFI pc_wdata. If the ID prediction was\n+  correct, EX suppresses the later redirect/flush; if it was wrong, the existing EX\n+  redirect path repairs the PC and flushes wrong-path state. This targets hot\n+  CoreMark loop backedges without adding branch-immediate decode or BTB lookup to\n+  the fetch next-PC path, trading a small ID/control-table cost for fewer recurring\n+  taken-branch bubbles.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC and prediction-valid metadata to IF/ID or ID/EX payloads so EX can validate an ID-stage target prediction without changing RVFI ports.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate and wire the ID-stage predictor redirect alongside the existing EX redirect, giving EX mispredict recovery priority and preserving nret=1 retirement semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consult the small learned target table using the IF/ID PC, emit an early redirect on a taken tag hit, and carry prediction metadata into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the resolved next PC with the ID prediction, suppress redundant correct-prediction redirects, and produce update information for taken/not-taken branch and jump outcomes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept the new early redirect input with the same flush discipline as existing redirects while keeping the ordinary pc+4 fetch path unchanged on non-predicted instructions.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r5s2\n+title: \"ID-stage learned target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because opcode/immediate decode,\n+  BTB comparisons, return-shape checks, and predicted-next-PC muxing were placed on\n+  the IF next-PC path. CoreMark still pays a two-instruction penalty on recurring\n+  taken loop branches and direct jumps, so the remaining promising predictor angle\n+  is to avoid the IF critical path while still reducing taken-control bubbles.\n+\n+  A predictor consulted in ID can use the already-fetched PC/instruction timing\n+  point and redirect one cycle earlier than the current EX resolver. It only saves\n+  one of the two wrong-path slots, but it should cost less Fmax than full IF\n+  speculation and does not require early operand compare or immediate generation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped learned target predictor that is read in ID rather than\n+  IF. EX remains the authoritative resolver and updates a small table with the PC,\n+  resolved target, and a 2-bit taken counter for valid branches and jumps. When an\n+  instruction reaches ID, the predictor checks the IF/ID PC against the table tag;\n+  on a taken hit it sends an early redirect to IF using the stored target and marks\n+  the ID/EX payload with the predicted next PC.\n+\n+  EX still computes the actual next PC and RVFI pc_wdata. If the ID prediction was\n+  correct, EX suppresses the later redirect/flush; if it was wrong, the existing EX\n+  redirect path repairs the PC and flushes wrong-path state. This targets hot\n+  CoreMark loop backedges without adding branch-immediate decode or BTB lookup to\n+  the fetch next-PC path, trading a small ID/control-table cost for fewer recurring\n+  taken-branch bubbles.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC and prediction-valid metadata to IF/ID or ID/EX payloads so EX can validate an ID-stage target prediction without changing RVFI ports.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate and wire the ID-stage predictor redirect alongside the existing EX redirect, giving EX mispredict recovery priority and preserving nret=1 retirement semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consult the small learned target table using the IF/ID PC, emit an early redirect on a taken tag hit, and carry prediction metadata into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the resolved next PC with the ID prediction, suppress redundant correct-prediction redirects, and produce update information for taken/not-taken branch and jump outcomes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept the new early redirect input with the same flush discipline as existing redirects while keeping the ordinary pc+4 fetch path unchanged on non-predicted instructions.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r5s2\n+title: \"ID-stage learned target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because opcode/immediate decode,\n+  BTB comparisons, return-shape checks, and predicted-next-PC muxing were placed on\n+  the IF next-PC path. CoreMark still pays a two-instruction penalty on recurring\n+  taken loop branches and direct jumps, so the remaining promising predictor angle\n+  is to avoid the IF critical path while still reducing taken-control bubbles.\n+\n+  A predictor consulted in ID can use the already-fetched PC/instruction timing\n+  point and redirect one cycle earlier than the current EX resolver. It only saves\n+  one of the two wrong-path slots, but it should cost less Fmax than full IF\n+  speculation and does not require early operand compare or immediate generation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped learned target predictor that is read in ID rather than\n+  IF. EX remains the authoritative resolver and updates a small table with the PC,\n+  resolved target, and a 2-bit taken counter for valid branches and jumps. When an\n+  instruction reaches ID, the predictor checks the IF/ID PC against the table tag;\n+  on a taken hit it sends an early redirect to IF using the stored target and marks\n+  the ID/EX payload with the predicted next PC.\n+\n+  EX still computes the actual next PC and RVFI pc_wdata. If the ID prediction was\n+  correct, EX suppresses the later redirect/flush; if it was wrong, the existing EX\n+  redirect path repairs the PC and flushes wrong-path state. This targets hot\n+  CoreMark loop backedges without adding branch-immediate decode or BTB lookup to\n+  the fetch next-PC path, trading a small ID/control-table cost for fewer recurring\n+  taken-branch bubbles.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC and prediction-valid metadata to IF/ID or ID/EX payloads so EX can validate an ID-stage target prediction without changing RVFI ports.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate and wire the ID-stage predictor redirect alongside the existing EX redirect, giving EX mispredict recovery priority and preserving nret=1 retirement semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consult the small learned target table using the IF/ID PC, emit an early redirect on a taken tag hit, and carry prediction metadata into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare the resolved next PC with the ID prediction, suppress redundant correct-prediction redirects, and produce update information for taken/not-taken branch and jump outcomes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept the new early redirect input with the same flush discipline as existing redirects while keeping the ordinary pc+4 fetch path unchanged on non-predicted instructions.\"\n","additions":42,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778664217467,"end":1778664217469}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_090e735e80e99ec6016a0442f42834819a9cc8036e448cc994"}},"id":"prt_e20a58ab6002UiMBJzC602Isy1","sessionID":"ses_1df5b2859ffeln6y4cMtuSf6LS","messageID":"msg_e20a51346001823LyQ3F20Hu9Q"}}
