{"type":"text","timestamp":1778666681432,"sessionID":"ses_1df34bd21ffeemsi6WUsr8fUNJ","part":{"id":"prt_e20cbb166001pxPlxUf3Ffc27Y","messageID":"msg_e20cb691a001EpbwjYFTijQ675","sessionID":"ses_1df34bd21ffeemsi6WUsr8fUNJ","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor attempts consistently lost Fmax when they added next-PC prediction, metadata, or table lookups to IF/ID. I’m going to propose a narrower predictor: a tiny branch-direction confidence filter used only to avoid unnecessary front-end flushes for strongly not-taken conditional branches, leaving the fetch next-PC path as `pc+4` and avoiding target prediction entirely.","time":{"start":1778666680678,"end":1778666681431},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a7d923b1e99ca2c016a044cb8906881989a830f6ab0752ff1","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778666691679,"sessionID":"ses_1df34bd21ffeemsi6WUsr8fUNJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_5BmG3UDqX6qmXIlNVLkbG6g7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Not-taken branch confidence predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because target prediction put\n+  tag checks, immediate decode, next-PC muxing, and speculation metadata on the\n+  fragile front-end path. The current core already fetches pc+4, which is the\n+  correct path for not-taken conditional branches; the remaining predictor\n+  opportunity is to make use of that cheap default without adding a target mux.\n+\n+  CoreMark contains a mix of loop backedges and forward conditional exits. A\n+  small direction-only confidence table can learn branches that are almost\n+  always not taken and let EX avoid asserting redirect/flush work for those\n+  correctly predicted fall-through cases, while taken branches and jumps keep\n+  using the existing authoritative EX redirect path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped direction predictor that stores only conditional\n+  branch PCs and 2-bit not-taken/taken confidence counters. IF still always\n+  presents pc+4 as the next fetch address; there is no predicted target path,\n+  no branch immediate decode in IF, and no speculative target metadata. ID only\n+  carries a single predicted_not_taken bit for conditional branches based on a\n+  PC tag hit and a not-taken counter state.\n+\n+  EX remains the authoritative resolver and updates the table after each valid\n+  conditional branch. For predicted-not-taken branches that are actually not\n+  taken, behavior is identical to the current pc+4 flow. For taken branches, EX\n+  uses the existing redirect/flush path and trains the counter toward taken.\n+  This deliberately targets a smaller CPI win than BTB-style prediction, but it\n+  should have much lower Fmax risk because the fetch next-PC cone is unchanged\n+  and the extra pipeline metadata is one bit.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add one predicted_not_taken bit to IF/ID and ID/EX metadata for conditional branches only.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the existing pc+4 next-PC path unchanged; optionally accept a branch-PC tag hit signal without adding any target muxing.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Read the small direction table using the current IF/ID PC and mark conditional branches that are confidently predicted not taken.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the direction counters on resolved conditional branches while preserving existing redirect behavior for all taken branches and jumps.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Not-taken branch confidence predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because target prediction put\n+  tag checks, immediate decode, next-PC muxing, and speculation metadata on the\n+  fragile front-end path. The current core already fetches pc+4, which is the\n+  correct path for not-taken conditional branches; the remaining predictor\n+  opportunity is to make use of that cheap default without adding a target mux.\n+\n+  CoreMark contains a mix of loop backedges and forward conditional exits. A\n+  small direction-only confidence table can learn branches that are almost\n+  always not taken and let EX avoid asserting redirect/flush work for those\n+  correctly predicted fall-through cases, while taken branches and jumps keep\n+  using the existing authoritative EX redirect path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped direction predictor that stores only conditional\n+  branch PCs and 2-bit not-taken/taken confidence counters. IF still always\n+  presents pc+4 as the next fetch address; there is no predicted target path,\n+  no branch immediate decode in IF, and no speculative target metadata. ID only\n+  carries a single predicted_not_taken bit for conditional branches based on a\n+  PC tag hit and a not-taken counter state.\n+\n+  EX remains the authoritative resolver and updates the table after each valid\n+  conditional branch. For predicted-not-taken branches that are actually not\n+  taken, behavior is identical to the current pc+4 flow. For taken branches, EX\n+  uses the existing redirect/flush path and trains the counter toward taken.\n+  This deliberately targets a smaller CPI win than BTB-style prediction, but it\n+  should have much lower Fmax risk because the fetch next-PC cone is unchanged\n+  and the extra pipeline metadata is one bit.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add one predicted_not_taken bit to IF/ID and ID/EX metadata for conditional branches only.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the existing pc+4 next-PC path unchanged; optionally accept a branch-PC tag hit signal without adding any target muxing.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Read the small direction table using the current IF/ID PC and mark conditional branches that are confidently predicted not taken.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the direction counters on resolved conditional branches while preserving existing redirect behavior for all taken branches and jumps.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,42 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Not-taken branch confidence predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because target prediction put\n+  tag checks, immediate decode, next-PC muxing, and speculation metadata on the\n+  fragile front-end path. The current core already fetches pc+4, which is the\n+  correct path for not-taken conditional branches; the remaining predictor\n+  opportunity is to make use of that cheap default without adding a target mux.\n+\n+  CoreMark contains a mix of loop backedges and forward conditional exits. A\n+  small direction-only confidence table can learn branches that are almost\n+  always not taken and let EX avoid asserting redirect/flush work for those\n+  correctly predicted fall-through cases, while taken branches and jumps keep\n+  using the existing authoritative EX redirect path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped direction predictor that stores only conditional\n+  branch PCs and 2-bit not-taken/taken confidence counters. IF still always\n+  presents pc+4 as the next fetch address; there is no predicted target path,\n+  no branch immediate decode in IF, and no speculative target metadata. ID only\n+  carries a single predicted_not_taken bit for conditional branches based on a\n+  PC tag hit and a not-taken counter state.\n+\n+  EX remains the authoritative resolver and updates the table after each valid\n+  conditional branch. For predicted-not-taken branches that are actually not\n+  taken, behavior is identical to the current pc+4 flow. For taken branches, EX\n+  uses the existing redirect/flush path and trains the counter toward taken.\n+  This deliberately targets a smaller CPI win than BTB-style prediction, but it\n+  should have much lower Fmax risk because the fetch next-PC cone is unchanged\n+  and the extra pipeline metadata is one bit.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add one predicted_not_taken bit to IF/ID and ID/EX metadata for conditional branches only.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the existing pc+4 next-PC path unchanged; optionally accept a branch-PC tag hit signal without adding any target muxing.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Read the small direction table using the current IF/ID PC and mark conditional branches that are confidently predicted not taken.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the direction counters on resolved conditional branches while preserving existing redirect behavior for all taken branches and jumps.\"\n","additions":42,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","time":{"start":17786666916