{"type":"text","timestamp":1778668588422,"sessionID":"ses_1df17b3eaffeg6KgacdXvefuak","part":{"id":"prt_e20e8ccf50010RDMMfE9NACPgF","messageID":"msg_e20e875aa001iw23Yc5i4UF5ti","sessionID":"ses_1df17b3eaffeg6KgacdXvefuak","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts all lost primarily by adding IF next-PC/table/metadata cost. The narrowest remaining predictor angle is static prediction for unconditional direct JAL only, moved to ID so it avoids IF-table lookup and conditional branch compare complexity.","time":{"start":1778668588277,"end":1778668588421},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03a2faf6cf98f9d6016a04542c2cf0819a9d1049c45bf862e5","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778668591543,"sessionID":"ses_1df17b3eaffeg6KgacdXvefuak","part":{"id":"prt_e20e8d97a001pTPfHPYqFT5lXp","messageID":"msg_e20e875aa001iw23Yc5i4UF5ti","sessionID":"ses_1df17b3eaffeg6KgacdXvefuak","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a low-risk predictor hypothesis that targets only direct unconditional jumps, with no learned table and no conditional branch prediction.","time":{"start":1778668591482,"end":1778668591542},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03a2faf6cf98f9d6016a04542f6130819a87607a5796002f21","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778668614127,"sessionID":"ses_1df17b3eaffeg6KgacdXvefuak","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_h6NBCNnKzw9JCvS2WLIXyL3b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r7s2\n+title: \"ID-stage JAL target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Every prior predictor attempt for this core regressed because it put too much\n+  work on the fragile fetch next-PC path or carried broad prediction metadata\n+  through the pipeline. CoreMark still contains direct calls and direct jumps\n+  that are always taken, and those currently wait until EX before redirecting,\n+  paying two wrong-path slots each time. A predictor slot should therefore focus\n+  on the smallest control-flow case with a guaranteed direction and encoded\n+  target.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a static ID-stage predictor for JAL only. Decode already computes the\n+  J-immediate in ID, so when IF/ID holds a valid JAL the ID stage can request an\n+  early redirect to pc+imm one cycle before the existing EX resolver. Carry a\n+  single predicted-direct-jump bit with the instruction so EX suppresses the\n+  duplicate redirect only for the matching JAL; all conditional branches, JALR,\n+  and misaligned target checks remain under the current authoritative EX path.\n+\n+  This avoids BTB/BHT state, tag comparators, return-stack logic, and IF-stage\n+  immediate decode while recovering one bubble for direct calls/jumps. The\n+  expected gain is modest but it is the predictor variant least likely to repeat\n+  the known Fmax regressions from broader front-end speculation.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add one ID/EX metadata bit indicating that a JAL already redirected in ID, without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect valid JAL in ID, compute pc+J-immediate using existing imm_gen output, emit an early redirect, and mark the ID/EX payload as already predicted.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage JAL redirect into the existing IF and hazard redirect paths with EX redirect priority for authoritative recovery.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress only the duplicate EX redirect for a JAL that was already redirected in ID, while preserving actual pc_next, misalignment trapping, and normal branch/JALR behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r7s2\n+title: \"ID-stage JAL target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Every prior predictor attempt for this core regressed because it put too much\n+  work on the fragile fetch next-PC path or carried broad prediction metadata\n+  through the pipeline. CoreMark still contains direct calls and direct jumps\n+  that are always taken, and those currently wait until EX before redirecting,\n+  paying two wrong-path slots each time. A predictor slot should therefore focus\n+  on the smallest control-flow case with a guaranteed direction and encoded\n+  target.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a static ID-stage predictor for JAL only. Decode already computes the\n+  J-immediate in ID, so when IF/ID holds a valid JAL the ID stage can request an\n+  early redirect to pc+imm one cycle before the existing EX resolver. Carry a\n+  single predicted-direct-jump bit with the instruction so EX suppresses the\n+  duplicate redirect only for the matching JAL; all conditional branches, JALR,\n+  and misaligned target checks remain under the current authoritative EX path.\n+\n+  This avoids BTB/BHT state, tag comparators, return-stack logic, and IF-stage\n+  immediate decode while recovering one bubble for direct calls/jumps. The\n+  expected gain is modest but it is the predictor variant least likely to repeat\n+  the known Fmax regressions from broader front-end speculation.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add one ID/EX metadata bit indicating that a JAL already redirected in ID, without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect valid JAL in ID, compute pc+J-immediate using existing imm_gen output, emit an early redirect, and mark the ID/EX payload as already predicted.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage JAL redirect into the existing IF and hazard redirect paths with EX redirect priority for authoritative recovery.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress only the duplicate EX redirect for a JAL that was already redirected in ID, while preserving actual pc_next, misalignment trapping, and normal branch/JALR behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/