{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778669578291,"sessionID":"ses_1df0851dcffeM08w41DUluFk0k","part":{"id":"prt_e20f7e832001G1iSdklOcZVt3I","messageID":"msg_e20f7e4b70019Gi569OkFYAEq9","sessionID":"ses_1df0851dcffeM08w41DUluFk0k","snapshot":"22dacd3016cbd9d552910ee0a5678871cf559f27","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778669593125,"sessionID":"ses_1df0851dcffeM08w41DUluFk0k","part":{"id":"prt_e20f81a280010y07PoIMT4kh4i","messageID":"msg_e20f7e4b70019Gi569OkFYAEq9","sessionID":"ses_1df0851dcffeM08w41DUluFk0k","type":"text","text":"The predictor history is consistently negative when adding IF/ID target paths, predictor tables, or metadata. I’m going to propose the narrowest remaining predictor variant: a branch-loop predictor that reuses the existing EX redirect path and only changes IF PC selection on an exact last-backedge hit, avoiding broad decode, counters, or multi-entry tables.","time":{"start":1778669591080,"end":1778669593124},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0338c9143d0559c9016a045816fbb48198904b279e9dace6dc","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778669615309,"sessionID":"ses_1df0851dcffeM08w41DUluFk0k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_S7BWIzuTHmY4QDjvpxy14cVt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Single backedge loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core lost fitness because they added IF\n+  decode, multi-entry tag/counter tables, return-stack checks, extra redirect\n+  sources, or broad predicted-next-PC metadata to a timing-sensitive front end.\n+  CoreMark still pays the full EX redirect penalty on hot counted-loop\n+  backedges, so the best predictor angle is a deliberately tiny loop-only\n+  target predictor that learns one recurring taken backward branch without\n+  touching direct jumps, returns, or forward branches.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry last-backedge predictor in if_stage. EX already computes\n+  the authoritative branch target and knows whether a conditional branch was\n+  taken; when that target is below the branch PC, record the branch PC and\n+  target in two registers. IF predicts only on an exact PC match to that one\n+  recorded backedge, selecting the registered target instead of pc+4.\n+\n+  To avoid repeating the prior predictor regressions, do not add a BHT, BTB\n+  array, return stack, IF immediate decode, or prediction metadata for jumps.\n+  Carry only a one-bit predicted_backedge flag and the predicted target through\n+  IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can suppress the duplicate redirect on a correct hit\n+  or use the existing redirect/flush recovery on mismatch. This focuses the\n+  hardware on the steady-state loop case most likely to help CoreMark while\n+  keeping the added comparison and muxing minimal.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-backedge metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX validation without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one learned backedge PC/target entry, predict only on exact PC match, and keep pc+4 as the default path for all other fetches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the learned backedge entry from taken backward conditional branches and suppress the normal redirect only when the one-entry prediction exactly matches the resolved target.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the learned-backedge update signals and predicted-backedge metadata between IF and EX while preserving the existing redirect recovery path.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Single backedge loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core lost fitness because they added IF\n+  decode, multi-entry tag/counter tables, return-stack checks, extra redirect\n+  sources, or broad predicted-next-PC metadata to a timing-sensitive front end.\n+  CoreMark still pays the full EX redirect penalty on hot counted-loop\n+  backedges, so the best predictor angle is a deliberately tiny loop-only\n+  target predictor that learns one recurring taken backward branch without\n+  touching direct jumps, returns, or forward branches.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry last-backedge predictor in if_stage. EX already computes\n+  the authoritative branch target and knows whether a conditional branch was\n+  taken; when that target is below the branch PC, record the branch PC and\n+  target in two registers. IF predicts only on an exact PC match to that one\n+  recorded backedge, selecting the registered target instead of pc+4.\n+\n+  To avoid repeating the prior predictor regressions, do not add a BHT, BTB\n+  array, return stack, IF immediate decode, or prediction metadata for jumps.\n+  Carry only a one-bit predicted_backedge flag and the predicted target through\n+  IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can suppress the duplicate redirect on a correct hit\n+  or use the existing redirect/flush recovery on mismatch. This focuses the\n+  hardware on the steady-state loop case most likely to help CoreMark while\n+  keeping the added comparison and muxing minimal.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-backedge metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX validation without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one learned backedge PC/target entry, predict only on exact PC match, and keep pc+4 as the default path for all other fetches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the learned backedge entry from taken backward conditional branches and suppress the normal redirect only when the one-entry prediction exactly matches the resolved target.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the learned-backedge update signals and predicted-backedge metadata between IF and EX while preserving the existing redirect recovery path.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hyp