{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778669621909,"sessionID":"ses_1df0851dcffeM08w41DUluFk0k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yJFhOEjxQ4ZypvRQ9duxqPbH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n2: title: \"Single backedge loop predictor\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Prior predictor attempts for this core lost fitness because they added IF\n6:   decode, multi-entry tag/counter tables, return-stack checks, extra redirect\n7:   sources, or broad predicted-next-PC metadata to a timing-sensitive front end.\n8:   CoreMark still pays the full EX redirect penalty on hot counted-loop\n9:   backedges, so the best predictor angle is a deliberately tiny loop-only\n10:   target predictor that learns one recurring taken backward branch without\n11:   touching direct jumps, returns, or forward branches.\n12: hypothesis: |\n13:   Add a single-entry last-backedge predictor in if_stage. EX already computes\n14:   the authoritative branch target and knows whether a conditional branch was\n15:   taken; when that target is below the branch PC, record the branch PC and\n16:   target in two registers. IF predicts only on an exact PC match to that one\n17:   recorded backedge, selecting the registered target instead of pc+4.\n18: \n19:   To avoid repeating the prior predictor regressions, do not add a BHT, BTB\n20:   array, return stack, IF immediate decode, or prediction metadata for jumps.\n21:   Carry only a one-bit predicted_backedge flag and the predicted target through\n22:   IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can suppress the duplicate redirect on a correct hit\n23:   or use the existing redirect/flush recovery on mismatch. This focuses the\n24:   hardware on the steady-state loop case most likely to help CoreMark while\n25:   keeping the added comparison and muxing minimal.\n26: expected_impact:\n27:   fitness_delta_pct: 1\n28:   confidence: low\n29: changes:\n30:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n31:     description: \"Add minimal predicted-backedge metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX validation without changing the nret=1 RVFI interface.\"\n32:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n33:     description: \"Add one learned backedge PC/target entry, predict only on exact PC match, and keep pc+4 as the default path for all other fetches.\"\n34:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n35:     description: \"Update the learned backedge entry from taken backward conditional branches and suppress the normal redirect only when the one-entry prediction exactly matches the resolved target.\"\n36:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n37:     description: \"Wire the learned-backedge update signals and predicted-backedge metadata between IF and EX while preserving the existing redirect recovery path.\"\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\ntitle: \"Single backedge loop predictor\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  Prior predictor attempts for this core lost fitness because they added IF\n  decode, multi-entry tag/counter tables, return-stack checks, extra redirect\n  sources, or broad predicted-next-PC metadata to a timing-sensitive front end.\n  CoreMark still pays the full EX redirect penalty on hot counted-loop\n  backedges, so the best predictor angle is a deliberately tiny loop-only\n  target predictor that learns one recurring taken backward branch without\n  touching direct jumps, returns, or forward branches.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a single-entry last-backedge predictor in if_stage. EX already computes\n  the authoritative branch target and knows whether a conditional branch was\n  taken; when that target is below the branch PC, record the branch PC and\n  target in two registers. IF predicts only on an exact PC match to that one\n  recorded backedge, selecting the registered target instead of pc+4.\n\n  To avoid repeating the prior predictor regressions, do not add a BHT, BTB\n  array, return stack, IF immediate decode, or prediction metadata for jumps.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778669621900,"end":1778669621908}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05a3a14107277465016a0458358900819b83b412786a1bedc8"}},"id":"prt_e20f89187001R0TR73Qi77NT64","sessionID":"ses_1df0851dcffeM08w41DUluFk0k","messageID":"msg_e20f87934001elg8giJwHNu91R"}}
