{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778670703333,"sessionID":"ses_1def7f2dbffeFbL4Ss6kml1oko","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_8wzoGaBiYlVfT3af3Hb1LZ7G","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Next-line backedge predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core resolves taken branches in EX and pays a two-instruction flush on every hot CoreMark loop backedge. Prior predictor attempts regressed because same-cycle IF decode, table reads, target muxes, and broad prediction metadata landed on the timing-sensitive fetch/control path. A predictor that prepares the likely next sequential PC one cycle ahead can target recurring backedges without putting a BTB lookup or immediate decode in the PC update cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry next-line backedge hint in if_stage. When EX resolves a taken conditional branch whose target is below its PC, record the branch PC and target. While fetching PC N, compare the recorded branch PC against N+4 and register a hint for the next sequential fetch; on the following cycle, if the PC is that hinted branch PC, select the already-registered target instead of pc+4.\n+\n+  EX remains the authoritative resolver and updates the hint only from valid resolved branches. Carry only a predicted_backedge bit and predicted target through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can suppress the duplicate redirect on a correct hit or use the existing redirect/flush path on mismatch. This is narrower than the previous backedge predictor because the table compare is for pc+4 in the prior cycle and the IF PC mux consumes only a registered valid/target hint, reducing critical-path risk while preserving RVFI pc_wdata/order semantics and the nret=1 interface.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted_backedge and predicted_target metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can validate the one-cycle-ahead hint.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Maintain a single learned backedge PC/target plus a registered next-line hint for pc+4, and use only the registered hint in the PC selection path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Report valid taken backward conditional branches to the predictor, compare actual next PC against the carried hint, and suppress redirects only on correct predictions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and predicted-control signals between IF and EX while keeping the single-channel RVFI port set unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Next-line backedge predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core resolves taken branches in EX and pays a two-instruction flush on every hot CoreMark loop backedge. Prior predictor attempts regressed because same-cycle IF decode, table reads, target muxes, and broad prediction metadata landed on the timing-sensitive fetch/control path. A predictor that prepares the likely next sequential PC one cycle ahead can target recurring backedges without putting a BTB lookup or immediate decode in the PC update cone.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry next-line backedge hint in if_stage. When EX resolves a taken conditional branch whose target is below its PC, record the branch PC and target. While fetching PC N, compare the recorded branch PC against N+4 and register a hint for the next sequential fetch; on the following cycle, if the PC is that hinted branch PC, select the already-registered target instead of pc+4.\n+\n+  EX remains the authoritative resolver and updates the hint only from valid resolved branches. Carry only a predicted_backedge bit and predicted target through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can suppress the duplicate redirect on a correct hit or use the existing redirect/flush path on mismatch. This is narrower than the previous backedge predictor because the table compare is for pc+4 in the prior cycle and the IF PC mux consumes only a registered valid/target hint, reducing critical-path risk while preserving RVFI pc_wdata/order semantics and the nret=1 interface.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted_backedge and predicted_target metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can validate the one-cycle-ahead hint.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Maintain a single learned backedge PC/target plus a registered next-line hint for pc+4, and use only the registered hint in the PC selection path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Report valid taken backward conditional branches to the predictor, compare actual next PC against the carried hint, and suppress redirects only on correct predictions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and predicted-control signals between IF and EX while keeping the single-channel RVFI port set unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-run