smatch. This is narrower than the previous backedge predictor because the table compare is for pc+4 in the prior cycle and the IF PC mux consumes only a registered valid/target hint, reducing critical-path risk while preserving RVFI pc_wdata/order semantics and the nret=1 interface.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted_backedge and predicted_target metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles so EX can validate the one-cycle-ahead hint.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Maintain a single learned backedge PC/target plus a registered next-line hint for pc+4, and use only the registered hint in the PC selection path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Report valid taken backward conditional branches to the predictor, compare actual next PC against the carried hint, and suppress redirects only on correct predictions.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and predicted-control signals between IF and EX while keeping the single-channel RVFI port set unchanged.\"\n","additions":21,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778670703328,"end":1778670703332}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0966a680a02d6609016a045c559578819ba744484f518edb5f"}},"id":"prt_e2108b3900015sV6HHOvNk4o1X","sessionID":"ses_1def7f2dbffeFbL4Ss6kml1oko","messageID":"msg_e2108a127001EXKN3iNNZeV3fR"}}
