{"type":"text","timestamp":1778676592017,"sessionID":"ses_1de9ecc0cffe0G79S3mVPj20U0","part":{"id":"prt_e2162ec90001MMKR17s4UZXu7c","messageID":"msg_e2162cf5a001EnvhGjzG1MGrNc","sessionID":"ses_1de9ecc0cffe0G79S3mVPj20U0","type":"text","text":"This formal invocation selected the dual-channel wrapper despite passing `checks_si.cfg`, so it failed before checking RTL because `io_rvfi_valid_1` does not exist for this `nret: 1` core. I’m checking the script interface and will rerun with the correct single-issue wrapper selector.","time":{"start":1778676591760,"end":1778676592015},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0503383560aa9756016a04736fa4988199a9236be1f90c8d23","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778676594525,"sessionID":"ses_1de9ecc0cffe0G79S3mVPj20U0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Vuf015HG4HS4zN9jCLdnxoDA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1/formal/run_all.sh","offset":1,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep1/cores/bench/worktrees/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1/formal/run_all.sh</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env bash\n2: # Run riscv-formal checks against the current $RTL_DIR/*.sv.\n3: # Requires: formal/riscv-formal cloned (manual clone or `git submodule init`).\n4: #\n5: # Stages every $RTL_DIR/*.sv plus wrapper.sv + the chosen checks config under\n6: # the riscv-formal tree, then runs sby -> bitwuzla via the framework's\n7: # generated makefile. Tallies PASS/FAIL by inspecting each task's\n8: # logfile.txt.\n9: #\n10: # Usage: bash formal/run_all.sh [checks-cfg-path]\n11: #   default: formal/checks.cfg       (fast, ALTOPS, used by orchestrator)\n12: #   deep   : formal/checks-deep.cfg  (no ALTOPS, proves M-ext arithmetic)\n13: #\n14: # Env vars (orchestrator-driven, override $1 and defaults):\n15: #   WRAPPER     — path to wrapper SV (default formal/wrapper.sv)\n16: #   CHECKS_CFG  — path to checks config (default formal/checks.cfg)\n17: # When BOTH are unset, the script auto-detects nret from\n18: # cores/$CORE_NAME/core.yaml: nret=1 routes to wrapper_si.sv +\n19: # checks_si.cfg; nret=2 (or absent) uses the defaults. Agents\n20: # invoking `bash formal/run_all.sh` directly therefore get the\n21: # right wrapper without needing to know the env-var plumbing.\n22: set -e\n23: \n24: if [ -z \"${RTL_DIR:-}\" ] || [ -z \"${CORE_NAME:-}\" ]; then\n25:   echo \"ERROR: formal/run_all.sh requires RTL_DIR and CORE_NAME env vars.\" >&2\n26:   echo \"  Example: RTL_DIR=cores/v1/rtl CORE_NAME=v1 bash formal/run_all.sh formal/checks.cfg\" >&2\n27:   exit 2\n28: fi\n29: \n30: SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")\" && pwd)\"\n31: PROJECT_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$SCRIPT_DIR/..\" && pwd)\"\n32: RISCV_FORMAL=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/riscv-formal\"\n33: # PID-suffixed work dir + log so two concurrent invocations (e.g., the\n34: # agent self-checking mid-implementation while the orchestrator runs\n35: # its end-of-iteration eval) don't race on `rm -rf checks/` or\n36: # truncate each other's last_run.log. Was observed live in the\n37: # nret=1 verify run: two slots got broken: make_failed_during_execution\n38: # because the agent invoked `bash formal/run_all.sh` 6+ times in quick\n39: # succession, each invocation wiping the previous one's checks/ dir\n40: # mid-SBY (yosys-smtbmc crashed with `FileNotFoundError: 'engine_0/trace0.vcd'`).\n41: # genchecks.py derives @core@ from cwd's basename (genchecks.py:39), so\n42: # the PID-suffixed dir maps cleanly to @core@=\"$CORE_NAME-$$\".\n43: CORE_DIR=\"$RISCV_FORMAL/cores/$CORE_NAME-$$\"\n44: LOG=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/last_run-$$.log\"\n45: \n46: # Auto-detect single-issue cores from core.yaml when WRAPPER + CHECKS_CFG\n47: # are both unset and $1 (checks-cfg-path) wasn't given either. Explicit\n48: # env vars or $1 still win. Uses python3 to parse YAML robustly — bash\n49: # grep would mis-handle quoted/indented variants and break on the next\n50: # yaml schema bump.\n51: CORE_YAML=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/cores/$CORE_NAME/core.yaml\"\n52: if [ -z \"${WRAPPER:-}\" ] && [ -z \"${CHECKS_CFG:-}\" ] && [ -z \"${1:-}\" ] \\\n53:    && [ -f \"$CORE_YAML\" ]; then\n54:     # Pass the path via env var so the python literal stays free of any\n55:     # bash-substituted strings that could break on quoting / spaces.\n56:     NRET=$(CORE_YAML=\"$CORE_YAML\" python3 -c '\n57: import os, yaml\n58: try:\n59:     d = yaml.safe_load(open(os.environ[\"CORE_YAML\"]).read()) or {}\n60:     print(int(d.get(\"nret\", 2)))\n61: except Exception:\n62:     print(2)\n63: ' 2>/dev/null)\n64:     if [ \"$NRET\" = \"1\" ]; then\n65:         WRAPPER=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/wrapper_si.sv\"\n66:         CHECKS_CFG=\"$SCRIPT_DIR/checks_si.cfg\"\n67:         echo \"[run_all.sh] auto-detected nret=1 from $CORE_YAML; using wrapper_si.sv + checks_si.cfg\"\n68:     fi\n69: fi\n70: \n71: CHECKS_CFG=\"${CHECKS_CFG:-${1:-$SCRIPT_DIR/checks.cfg}}\"\n72: WRAPPER=\"${WRAPPER:-$SCRIPT_DIR/wrapper.sv}\"\n73: if [ ! -f \"$CHECKS_CFG\" ]; then\n74:     echo \"ERROR: checks.cfg not found at $CHECKS_CFG\"\n75:     exit 1\n76: fi\n77: if [ ! -f \"$WRAPPER\" ]; then\n78:     echo \"ERROR: wrapper not found at $WRAPPER\"\n79:     exit 1\n80: fi\n81: \n82: if [ ! -d \"$RISCV_FORMAL\" ]; then\n83:     echo \"ERROR: formal/riscv-formal not found. Clone it:\"\n84:     echo \"  git clone https://github.com/YosysHQ/riscv-formal $SCRIPT_DIR/riscv-formal\"\n85:     exit 1\n86: fi\n87: \n88: # OSS CAD Suite for consistent yosys / sby / bitwuzla. Homebrew yosys\n89: # combined with Homebrew bitwuzla has been observed to BrokenPipe inside\n90: # yosys-smtbmc.\n91: if [ -d \"$PROJECT_ROOT/.toolchain/oss-cad-suite/bin\" ]; then\n92:     export PATH=\"$PROJECT_ROOT/.toolchain/oss-cad-suite/bin:$PATH\"\n93: fi\n94: \n95: # Reap stale per-PID work dirs + logs whose owning process has exited.\n96: # Bounds disk growth from long runs (an agent that invokes run_all.sh\n97: # dozens of times leaves dozens of $CORE_NAME-<pid>/ dirs otherwise).\n98: # kill -0 returns 0 iff <pid> exists; non-existent / non-numeric names\n99: # fall through to cleanup. Concurrent live runs are protected because\n100: # their PIDs are still alive.\n101: shopt -s nullglob\n102: for stale in \"$RISCV_FORMAL/cores/$CORE_NAME-\"*; do\n103:     pid=\"${stale##*-}\"\n104:     if [[ \"$pid\" =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]] && ! kill -0 \"$pid\" 2>/dev/null; then\n105:         rm -rf \"$stale\"\n106:     fi\n107: done\n108: for stale_log in \"$SCRIPT_DIR\"/last_run-*.log; do\n109:     pid=\"${stale_log##*-}\"\n110:     pid=\"${pid%.log}\"\n111:     if [[ \"$pid\" =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]] && ! kill -0 \"$pid\" 2>/dev/null; then\n112:         rm -f \"$stale_log\"\n113:     fi\n114: done\n115: shopt -u nullglob\n116: \n117: # Truncate the run log; genchecks + make are tee'd here in full.\n118: : > \"$LOG\"\n119: \n120: # Stage rtl + wrapper + the chosen checks config under the framework's\n121: # expected layout. genchecks.py looks for \"checks.cfg\" by name, so the\n122: # selected config is always copied to that filename in the core dir.\n123: mkdir -p \"$CORE_DIR\"\n124: # Clear stale .sv files first. Without this, a hypothesis that renames or\n125: # deletes a module in rtl/ leaves a ghost copy in $CORE_DIR from the\n126: # previous run, and genchecks/yosys silently picks up the old file\n127: # instead of the new one. CLAUDE.md explicitly grants hypotheses the\n128: # right to rename/delete files in rtl/, so this cleanup is required.\n129: rm -f \"$CORE_DIR\"/*.sv\n130: cp \"$PROJECT_ROOT/$RTL_DIR\"/*.sv \"$CORE_DIR/\"\n131: cp \"$WRAPPER\"                   \"$CORE_DIR/wrapper.sv\"\n132: \n133: # Stage checks.cfg with [verilog-files] auto-derived from actual rtl/\n134: # contents instead of the cfg's hardcoded list. The shipped checks.cfg\n135: # enumerates the V0 baseline filenames; CLAUDE.md grants hypotheses the\n136: # right to add new modules, split a stage into multiple files, or rename\n137: # files in rtl/. Hardcoding silently fails on those restructurings (or\n138: # elaborates a stale ghost). Strip the original [verilog-files] section\n139: # and rebuild from the glob, with core_pkg.sv first and wrapper.sv last.\n140: STAGED_CFG=\"$CORE_DIR/checks.cfg\"\n141: awk '/^\\[verilog-files\\]/{exit} {print}' \"$CHECKS_CFG\" > \"$STAGED_CFG\"\n142: {\n143:     echo \"[verilog-files]\"\n144:     [ -f \"$CORE_DIR/core_pkg.sv\" ] && \\\n145:         echo \"@basedir@/cores/@core@/core_pkg.sv\"\n146:     for f in \"$CORE_DIR\"/*.sv; do\n147:         name=\"$(basename \"$f\")\"\n148:         [ \"$name\" = \"core_pkg.sv\" ] && continue\n149:         [ \"$name\" = \"wrapper.sv\" ] && continue\n150:         echo \"@basedir@/cores/@core@/$name\"\n151:     done\n152:     echo \"@basedir@/cores/@core@/wrapper.sv\"\n153: } >> \"$STAGED_CFG\"\n154: \n155: # genchecks.py derives @core@ from the cwd's basename (genchecks.py:39),\n156: # so cd-ing into $CORE_DIR (= $RISCV_FORMAL/cores/$CORE_NAME-$$) yields\n157: # @core@=\"$CORE_NAME-$$\". The [verilog-files] lines we just wrote\n158: # reference that @core@, so all paths resolve into this PID-private dir.\n159: cd \"$CORE_DIR\"\n160: rm -rf checks/\n161: echo \"=== genchecks ===\" | tee -a \"$LOG\"\n162: python3 ../../checks/genchecks.py >> \"$LOG\" 2>&1\n163: cd checks\n164: \n165: JOBS=\"${JOBS:-$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu 2>/dev/null || nproc 2>/dev/null || echo 4)}\"\n166: echo \"=== make -j$JOBS -k ===\" | tee -a \"$LOG\"\n167: # Tee full output to LOG; show filtered progress on stdout. `-k` keeps\n168: # going past per-check errors so the .sby tally below sees every result\n169: # (NRET=2 means a few `_ch1` checks may PREUNSAT-error on single-issue\n170: # cores; without -k make stops on first error and 95+ checks never run,\n171: # producing a misleading failure list of unbuilt directories).\n172: make -j\"$JOBS\" -k -f makefile 2>&1 \\\n173:     | tee -a \"$LOG\" \\\n174:     | grep -E \"^(make|SBY|yosys|==|ERROR)\" || true\n175: \n176: shopt -s nullglob\n177: PASS=0; FAIL=0; FAILED=()\n178: for sby_file in *.sby; do\n179:     name=\"${sby_file%.sby}\"\n180:     log=\"$name/logfile.txt\"\n\n(Showing lines 1-180 of 220. Use offset=181 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Run riscv-formal checks against the current $RTL_DIR/*.sv.\n# Requires: formal/riscv-formal cloned (manual clone or `git submodule init`).\n#\n# Stages every $RTL_DIR/*.sv plus wrapper.sv + the chosen checks config under\n# the riscv-formal tree, then runs sby -> bitwuzla via the framework's\n# generated makefile. Tallies PASS/FAIL by inspecting each task's\n# logfile.txt.\n#\n# Usage: bash formal/run_all.sh [checks-cfg-path]\n#   default: formal/checks.cfg       (fast, ALTOPS, used by orchestrator)\n#   deep   : formal/checks-deep.cfg  (no ALTOPS, proves M-ext arithmetic)\n#\n# Env vars (orchestrator-driven, override $1 and defaults):\n#   WRAPPER     — path to wrapper SV (default formal/wrapper.sv)\n#   CHECKS_CFG  — path to checks config (default formal/checks.cfg)\n# When BOTH are unset, the script auto-detects nret from\n# cores/$CORE_NAME/core.yaml: nret=1 routes to wrapper_si.sv +\n# checks_si.cfg; nret=2 (or absent) uses the defaults. Agents\n# invoking `bash formal/run_all.sh` directly therefore get the","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"formal/run_all.sh","time":{"start":1778676594518,"end":1778676594524}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0503383560aa9756016a04736fea188199ab3d9fa141c0551b"}},"id":"prt_e2162ed910015OZgvIpGeHZDGT","sessionID":"ses_1de9ecc0cffe0G79S3mVPj20U0","messageID":"msg_e2162cf5a001EnvhGjzG1MGrNc"}}
